<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000059.tif" N="7, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS I.</HEAD>
<HEAD>[<I>Primus passus de visione</I>.]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Primus, &amp;c</I>.] <I>found in</I> TUD.</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>What &thorn;is Mountein be-Mene&thorn; &middot; and &thorn;is derke Dale,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bemene&thorn;</I>] meni&thorn; TD; may mene U. <I>&thorn;is darke</I>] &thorn;is deope H; ek &thorn;e derke TD.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;is feire feld, ful of folk &middot; feire I schal ow schewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>feire feld</I>] THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D <I>omit</I> feire; <I>but see prol</I>. l. 17.</NOTE></L>
<L>A louely ladi on leor &middot; In linnene I-clo&thorn;ed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on leor</I>] of lire THUD; of lore H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>I-clo&thorn;ed</I>] was clothid U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Com a-doun from &thorn;e [clyf] &middot; and clepte me feire,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>clyf</I>] <I>so in</I> UDH<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>and</I> H <I>have</I> loft; T <I>reads</I> fro &thorn;at ki&thorn;. <I>clepte</I>] clepid H; callide TUH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>And seide, "sone! slepest &thorn;ou? &middot; Sixt &thorn;ou &thorn;is peple<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>slepest &thorn;ou</I>] slepistow U. <I>sixt</I>] sest T; seest HUD.</NOTE></L>
<L>Al hou bisy &thorn;ei ben &middot; A-boute &thorn;e Mase?</L>
<L>&THORN;e moste parti of &thorn;e peple &middot; &thorn;at passe&thorn; nou on eor&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nou on</I>] on &thorn;is TH<SUB>2</SUB>; vpon HU; here on D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hauen heo worschupe in &thorn;is world &middot; kepe &thorn;ei no betere;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in &thorn;is</I>] of &thorn;is HD; of &thorn;e U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="9">Of o&thorn;er heuene &thorn;en heer &middot; [holde] &thorn;ei no tale."<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>holde</I>] <I>so in</I> TUDH<SUB>2</SUB>; &yogh;eue&thorn; V; &yogh;yue H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Ich was a-ferd of hire Face &middot; &thorn;auh heo feir weore,</L>
<L>And seide, "Merci, Ma dame &middot; What is &thorn;is to mene?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is &thorn;is to mene</I>] may &thorn;is by|meene HU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">&para; "&THORN;is Tour and &thorn;is Toft," quod heo &middot; "treu&thorn;e is &thorn;er|Inne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and &thorn;is</I>] of &thorn;e T; on &thorn;e HDH<SUB>2</SUB>; in &thorn;e U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And wolde &thorn;at &yogh;e wrou&yogh;ten &middot; as his word teche&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] he H; &thorn;at U; D <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>For he is Fader of Fei &middot; &thorn;at formed ow alle<MILESTONE N="395a:2" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Fei</I>] fei&thorn; THUD. <I>ow</I>] &yogh;ow TUH<SUB>2</SUB>D; &yogh;ou H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e with Fel and with Face &middot; and &yogh;af ow fyue wittes,</L>
<L>Forte worschupen him [&thorn;erwith] &middot; while &yogh;e beo&thorn; heere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Forte</I>] For to THH<SUB>2</SUB>DU. [<I>&thorn;er|wi&thorn;</I>] V <I>omits this word; but it occurs in</I> THUH<SUB>2</SUB>; D <I>has</I> with.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000060.tif" N="8, A-text"></L>
<L N="17">And for he hihte &thorn;e eor&thorn;e &middot; to seruen ow vchone<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for&mdash;eor&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;erfore he bad &yogh;ow eche U. <I>for he hihte</I>] therefore hooteth H; &thorn;erfore he hi&yogh;te TH<SUB>2</SUB>D. <I>to&mdash;uchone</I>] to helpe &yogh;ow ichone TDH<SUB>2</SUB>; an helpen o&thorn;er U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of wollene, Of linnene &middot; To lyflode at neode,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Of&mdash;of</I>] And wollen &amp; D.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Mesurable Maner &middot; to maken ow at ese;</L>
<L N="20">And Comaundet of his Cortesye &middot; In Comune &thorn;reo &thorn;inges;</L>
<L>Heore nomes be&thorn; neodful &middot; and nempnen hem I &thorn;enke,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Heore&mdash;neodful</I>] Narn (Are H<SUB>2</SUB>) none nedful but &thorn;o TH<SUB>2</SUB>; Arn non nedful but &thorn;ei U; Ne arn non nedful but &thorn;o D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bi Rule and bi Resun &middot; Rehersen hem her-aftur.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bi&mdash;bi</I>] And rekne hem in TD; And rekene hem be H<SUB>2</SUB>; And rekne hem &yogh;ow by U. <I>Rehersen</I>] reherse &thorn;ou TD; reherse &yogh;ow H<SUB>2</SUB>; reherce &yogh;e U. <I>heraftur</I>] aftir UD.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;at on Clothing is &middot; from Chele ow to saue:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>clo&thorn;ing is</I>] is vesture TH<SUB>2</SUB>; is vesture verrailiche U. <I>from chele</I>] fro cold U. <I>ow</I>] &thorn;e TH<SUB>2</SUB>. D <I>reads</I>, That on is clo&thorn;ing for cold &middot; &thorn;at it may &thorn;ee saue.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">And &thorn;at o&thorn;ur Mete at Meel &middot; for meseise of &thorn;iseluen:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And&mdash;meel</I>] &thorn;e to&thorn;er is mete at &yogh;our meel U. <I>meseise</I>] myschief UH. <I>&thorn;iseluen</I>] &yogh;ow selue U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And drink whon &thorn;ou drui&yogh;est &middot; but do hit not out of Resun,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ow drui&yogh;est</I>] &thorn;e dri&yogh;e&thorn; TH<SUB>2</SUB>; &yogh;ow drieth U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ou weor[&thorn;]e &thorn;e worse &middot; whon &thorn;ou worche scholdest.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ou weore</I>] &thorn;ou wor&thorn;e THD; &thorn;e worth H<SUB>2</SUB>; &yogh;e wurche U. <I>&thorn;ou&mdash;scholdest</I>] &yogh;e swynke scholde U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; For Lot in his lyf-dayes &middot; for lyking of drinke,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for lyking</I>] &thorn;orou&yogh; lykynge H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">Dude bi his douhtren &middot; &thorn;at &thorn;e deuel louede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>louede</I>] lykide THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Dilytede him in drinke &middot; as &thorn;e deuel wolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>T <I>omits this line; but it occurs in</I> H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>as well as in</I> HD <I>and</I> U.</P><P>OBS. A whole folio is here lost out of U; from l. 33 down to l. 99.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>And lecherie him lauhte &middot; and lay bi hem bo&thorn;e;</L>
<L>And al he witede hit wyn &middot; &thorn;at wikkede dede.</L>
<L N="32">Dreede dilitable drinke &middot; And &thorn;ou schalt do &thorn;e bettre;</L>
<L>Mesure is Medicine &middot; &thorn;auh &thorn;ou muche &yogh;eor[n]e.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;eorne</I>] V &yogh;eore; <I>but</I> T <I>has</I> &yogh;erne; <I>so</I> H <I>and</I> D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Al nis not good to &thorn;e gost &middot; &thorn;at &thorn;e bodi lyke&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bodi</I>] gut TD; gutt H<SUB>2</SUB>; <I>which is perhaps a better reading, as regards the alliteration. lyke&thorn;</I>] aske&thorn; HH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne lyflode to &thorn;e licam &middot; &thorn;at leof is to &thorn;e soule.</L>
<L N="36">&para; Leef not &thorn;i licam &middot; for ly&yogh;ere him teche&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ly&yogh;ere</I>] lyar H; a li&thorn;er T; a lyere H<SUB>2</SUB>; a leder D. <I>teche&thorn;</I>] ledith H.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000061.tif" N="9, A-text"></L>
<L>&THORN;at is &thorn;e Wikkede word &middot; &thorn;e to bi-traye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wikkede</I>] wrecchide TH<SUB>2</SUB>D. <I>word</I>] world THH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;e Fend and &thorn;i Flesch &middot; folewen to-gedere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>folewen</I>] folowe&thorn; &thorn;ee H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And schende&thorn; &thorn;i soule &middot; seo hit in &thorn;in herte;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seo</I>] set T; I see H; &amp; set D; and seith H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="40">And for &thorn;ou scholdest beo war &middot; I wisse &thorn;e &thorn;e bettre.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bettre</I>] best HTH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"AMadame, Merci!" qua&thorn; I &middot; "me like&thorn; wel &thorn;i wordes.</L>
<L>Bote &thorn;e Moneye on &thorn;is Molde &middot; &thorn;at men so faste holden,</L>
<L>Tel me to whom &thorn;at Tresour appende&thorn;?"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="44">"GO to &thorn;e gospel," qua&thorn; heo &middot; "&thorn;at god sei&thorn; him|seluen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at god</I>] &thorn;er god H. <I>sei&thorn;</I>] seyde HD.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whon &thorn;e peple him a-posede &middot; with a peny in &thorn;e Temple,</L>
<L>&YOGH;if heo schulden worschupe &thorn;er-with &middot; Cesar heore kyng.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heo schulden</I>] &thorn;ei wile T. <I>heore</I>] &thorn;e TD.</NOTE></L>
