<L N="48">And whom &thorn;e ymage was lyk &middot; &thorn;at &thorn;er-Inne stod.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And&mdash;lyk</I>] And &thorn;e imagis like T; And ymage lyk DH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>stod</I>] standis T; stondeth HH<SUB>2</SUB>; standes D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "Ceesar, &thorn;ei seiden &middot; We seo&thorn; wel vchone."<Q>[<I>Reddite ergo que sunt cesaris cesari, et que sunt dei deo</I>.]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>The Latin quotation following is found in</I> H.</NOTE></L>
<L>"&thorn;enne <I>Reddite</I>," qua&thorn; God &middot; "&thorn;at to Cesar falle&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;enne Reddite</I>] Reddite cesari TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; &yogh;elde&thorn; to cesar H. <I>falle&thorn;</I>] befalle TH<SUB>2</SUB> (<I>which also om</I>. to); apendi&thorn; H; he longe&thorn; (be-longe&thorn;?) D.</NOTE></L>
<L><I>Et que sunt dei deo</I> &middot; or elles do &yogh;e ille."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Et&mdash;deo</I>] &amp; to god his deel H; Et que sunt dei digno D. <I>do &yogh;e</I>] &yogh;e don THH<SUB>2</SUB>; <I>also</I> D (<I>which om</I>. elles).</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">For Rihtfoliche Resoun &middot; schulde rulen ou alle,</L>
<L>And kuynde wit be wardeyn &middot; oure weol&thorn;e to kepe,</L>
<L>And tour of vr tresour &middot; to take hit [&yogh;ow] at nede;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>tour</I>] toure H; tutour TH<SUB>2</SUB>D. [<I>&yogh;ow</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>; &yogh;ou HD] V <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>For husbondrie and he &middot; holden to-gedere."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he</I>] witte H.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="56">&THORN;Enne I fraynede hire feire &middot; for him &thorn;at hire made,</L>
<L>"&THORN;at [dungun] in &thorn;at deope dale &middot; &thorn;at dredful is of siht,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at&mdash;dale</I>] &thorn;e dungeon in &thorn;e dale TDH<SUB>2</SUB>; &thorn;e dale &amp; &thorn;e dongown H. [<I>dungun</I>] V <I>has</I> doun; <I>but see prol</I>. l. 15.</NOTE></L>
<L>What may hit Mene, Madame &middot; Ich &thorn;e bi-seche?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hit mene</I>] &thorn;at bymeene H.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000062.tif" N="10, A-text"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"&THORN;At is &thorn;e Castel of care," quod heo &middot; "hose come&thorn; &thorn;er-Inne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>quod heo</I>] TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>and</I> D <I>omit. hose</I>] who &thorn;at THH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">Mai Banne &thorn;at he born was &middot; to Bodi or to soule.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-Inne wone&thorn; a wiht &middot; &thorn;at wrong is I-hote,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wiht</I>] wy TH<SUB>2</SUB>; wey D.</NOTE></L>
