<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000069.tif" N="17, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS II.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>Title; <I>found in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>UD; H <I>has</I> Ter|cius Passus <I>by mistake, as it also calls the next Passus by the same name</I>.</P><P>OBS. The first 23 lines occur <I>twice</I> in U; readings from the <I>fragment</I> are distinguished by the italic letter <I>U</I>.</P></NOTE>[<I>Passus secundus de visione</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Yit kneled I on my knees &middot; and cried hire of grace,<MILESTONE N="395b:2" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cried</I>] prayed H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And seide, "Merci, Madame &middot; for Maries loue of heuene<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Merci, Madame</I>] V <I>has</I> Madame Merci, <I>with marks for transposition</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Bar &thorn;e blisful Barn &middot; &thorn;at bou&yogh;t vs on &thorn;e Roode,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>blisful</I>] blisside TU; blessyd D. <I>on &thorn;e Roode</I>] wi&thorn; his blood H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Teche me &thorn;e kuynde craft &middot; forte knowe &thorn;e false."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Teche&mdash;kuynde</I>] kenne me be sum TU <I>U</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>D; teche me by kynde H. <I>forte knowe</I>] to kenne TH<SUB>2</SUB>; to knowe U <I>U</I> D.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Loke on &thorn;e lufthond," quod heo &middot; "and seo wher [he] stonde&thorn;!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lufthond</I>] left <I>U;</I> left half TU. <I>quod heo</I>] TDU <I>omit;</I> quod sche <I>U. seo</I>] lo TH<SUB>2</SUB>. [<I>he</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>D] &thorn;ei H <I>U;</I> V <I>has</I> heo.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e Fals and Fauuel &middot; and al his hole Meyne!"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>his</I>] her H. <I>al&mdash;Meyne</I>] hise feris manye TU <I>U</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>I lokede on &thorn;e luft half &middot; as &thorn;e ladi me tauhte;</L>
<L N="8">&THORN;enne was I war of a wommon &middot; wonderliche clo&thorn;ed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>clo&thorn;ed</I>] atired <I>U;</I> clothid U.</P><P>OBS. <I>After</I> clo&thorn;ed H <I>inserts</I>, In reed scarlet heo rode &middot; rybande wi&thorn; gold (<I>see</I> l. 13).</P></NOTE></L>
<L>Purfylet with pelure &middot; &thorn;e ricchest vppon eor&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>ricchest vppon</I>] pureste on U <I>U</I> D; purest in H<SUB>2</SUB>.</P><P>OBS. <I>Here</I> H <I>inserts</I>, py&yogh;te ful of perrye &middot; &amp; of preciouse stoones (<I>see</I> l. 12).</P></NOTE></L>
<L>I-Corouned with a Coroune &middot; &thorn;e kyng ha&thorn; no bettre;</L>
<L>Alle hir Fyue Fyngres &middot; weore frettet with Rynges,<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits this line; so also does U</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">Of &thorn;e preciousest perre &middot; &thorn;at prince wered euere;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>preciousest</I>] pureste TU <I>U</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>D. H <I>reads</I>.</P><P>Of reed gold so ryche &middot; redilyche I-dy&yogh;te</P><P>Wi&thorn; preciouse stoones so stoute &middot; stond|ynge &thorn;er-ynne.</P></NOTE>
<PB REF="00000070.tif" N="18, A-text"></L>
<L>In Red Scarlet heo Rod &middot; I-Rybaunt with gold;<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>inserts above; see obs. on</I> l. 8. <I>heo rod</I>] robid TU UD; robe H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>I|Rybaunt</I>] &amp; ribande TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; rybanyd U <I>U</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er nis no Qweene qweyntore &middot; &thorn;at quik is alyue.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nis</I>] is HU <I>U. qweyntore</I>] koynter H. <I>alyue</I>] on lyue HU <I>U</I> DH<SUB>2</SUB>; o lyue T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "What is &thorn;is wommon," quod I &middot; "&thorn;us wonderliche A-tyret?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wonderliche</I>] wor&thorn;ily TH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">&para; "&THORN;at is Meede &thorn;e Mayden," quod heo &middot; "&thorn;at ha&thorn; me marred ofte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>quod heo</I>] TU <I>U</I> DH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit. me marred</I>] noi&yogh;ede me ful T <I>U</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>; anoy&yogh;ed me H; noyed me wol U; noyed me wel D.</NOTE></L>
<L>A[n]d I-lakked my lore &middot; to lordes aboute.</L>
<L>In &thorn;e pope paleys heo is &middot; as priue as my-seluen;</L>
<L>And so schulde heo nou&yogh;t &middot; for wrong was hir syre;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heo nou&yogh;t</I>] it not be TD.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20">[Out of] wrong heo wox &middot; to wro&thorn;erhele monye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>U omits this line</I>. [<I>Out of</I> TH UH<SUB>2</SUB>D] V <I>has</I> In-to; U <I>reads</I>, Out of wrong wente sche &middot; wrotherhele manye.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich ouhte ben herre &thorn;en heo &middot; I com of a bettre.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>herre</I>] hi&yogh;ere T; hey&yogh;er H; heyere U <I>U</I> D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; To-morwe wor&thorn; &thorn;e Mariage I-mad &middot; Of Meede and of fals;</L>
<L>Fauuel with feir speche &middot; ha&thorn; brou&yogh;t hem to-gedere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>brou&yogh;t</I>] forgid TU <I>U</I> DH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">And Gyle ha&thorn; bi-gon hire so &middot; heo graunte&thorn; al his wille;<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And al is li&yogh;eres ledynge &middot; &thorn;at heo leuen to-gedere.<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>leuen</I>] li&yogh;en TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; lyue so H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; To-Morwe worth &thorn;e Mariage I-mad &middot; so&thorn; as I &thorn;e telle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>To-Morwe&mdash;I-mad</I>] To-morne schal &thorn;ei make &thorn;e mariage H. <I>so&thorn;</I>] TUH<SUB>2</SUB>D <I>omit;</I> D <I>also om</I>. I-mad.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ou miht [wyte] &yogh;if &thorn;ou wolt &middot; whuche &thorn;ei ben alle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at&mdash;wolt</I>] &thorn;ere mi&yogh;te &thorn;ou wyte &yogh;if &thorn;ou wilt (wolt H) THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D; V <I>has</I> seo <I>instead of</I> wyte.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">[&THORN;at longith to &thorn;at lordschipe &middot; &thorn;e lasse and &thorn;e more.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> U; <I>also in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; V <I>has only l</I>. 30, <I>running thus</I>, Bote &yogh;if &thorn;ow wilne to wone &middot; with treu&thorn;e in his Blisse, <I>with which</I> H <I>closely agrees</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Know hem &thorn;ere &yogh;if &thorn;ou canst &middot; and kepe &thorn;e fro hem alle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> U; <I>also in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; V <I>has only l</I>. 30, <I>running thus</I>, Bote &yogh;if &thorn;ow wilne to wone &middot; with treu&thorn;e in his Blisse, <I>with which</I> H <I>closely agrees</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;if &thorn;ou wilnest to wone &middot; with treuthe in his blisse;]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> U; <I>also in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>D; V <I>has only l</I>. 30, <I>running thus</I>, Bote &yogh;if &thorn;ow wilne to wone &middot; with treu&thorn;e in his Blisse, <I>with which</I> H <I>closely agrees</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>[lerne his lawe &thorn;at is so lele &middot; &amp; si&thorn;&thorn;e teche it fur&thorn;er.]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>This occurs in</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="19, A-text"></L>
<L N="32">I may no lengore lette &middot; vr lord Ich &thorn;e bi-kenne;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lette</I>] lende H; dwelle D. <I>vr</I>] TD <I>and</I> U <I>omit. bi-kenne</I>] by-take H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bi-come a good mon &middot; for eny couetyse, ich rede."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] Loke &thorn;ou H. <I>ich rede</I>] H <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>[When heo was me fro &middot; I loked &amp; byhelde]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Occurs in</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Alle &thorn;is Riche [Retenaunce] &middot; &thorn;at Regneden with Fals<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>Retenaunce</I> THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D] Rete|nauntes V. <I>&thorn;at</I>&mdash;<I>Fals</I>] &thorn;at with false reigneth U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">Weoren bede to &thorn;e Bruyt-ale &middot; on Bo two &thorn;e sydes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bruyt-ale</I>] bedale T; bridale UHH<SUB>2</SUB>D. <I>Bo two &thorn;e</I>] bo&thorn;e two THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Sir Simonye is of-sent &middot; to asseale &thorn;e Chartres,<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits. is of-sent</I>] is assent T; is a-sent H<SUB>2</SUB>; was aftur sent H; is A-sert D. <I>asseale</I>] a-sele T: seele H; ensele H<SUB>2</SUB>; sele D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Fals o&thorn;ur Fauuel &middot; bi eny [fyn] heolden,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>fyn</I>] THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D; V <I>has</I> peyne.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Feffe Meede &thorn;er-with &middot; In Mariage for euere.</L>
<L N="40">&para; Bote &thorn;er nas halle ne hous &middot; &thorn;at miht herborwe &thorn;e peple,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at miht</I>] to THUH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at vche feld nas ful &middot; of Folk al a-boute.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nas</I>] was D. <I>ful</I>] filled H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; In middes on a Mountayne &middot; at Midmorwe tyde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] of HD; T <I>and</I> U <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Was piht vp a Pauilon &middot; A Proud for &thorn;e nones;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A proud</I>] prow U; T <I>and</I> U <I>omit</I> A; was proud D.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">And Ten &thorn;ousend of Tentes &middot; I-tilled be-sydes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I-tilled</I>] I-teldyde for&thorn; H; teldit TH<SUB>2</SUB>; tight &thorn;er U; teled D.</NOTE></L>
<L>For knihtes of Cuntre &middot; and Comers aboute,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] Of TUD. <I>and Comers</I>] of comeres TUH<SUB>2</SUB>D.</NOTE></L>
