<L N="224">And flatte on his face &middot; and faste on him cri&yogh;ede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And flatte</I>] heo flat H; And flattide it T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And seide, "war &thorn;e for wonhope &middot; &thorn;at Wol &thorn;e bi-traye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>war &thorn;e for</I>] &thorn;at H. <I>&thorn;at&mdash;&thorn;e</I>] wile &thorn;e T; wolde hym H; he wil &thorn;e U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; 'Icham sori for my sunnes' &middot; sei to &thorn;i-seluen,<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits this line</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bet &thorn;i-self on &thorn;e Breste &middot; and bidde god of grace,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;y H. <I>god</I>] hym TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>For nis no gult her so gret &middot; his Merci nis wel more."<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits. For</I>] &thorn;er H. <I>her</I>] H <I>omits. his</I>] &thorn;at H. <I>his&mdash;more</I>] &thorn;at his goodnesse nis more T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="229">&para; &THORN;enne sat sleu&thorn;e vp &middot; and sikede sore,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sikede sore</I>] seide to hymsiluen H; seynide hym faste TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And made a-vou bi-fore god &middot; for his foule sleu&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bifore</I>] tofore T; to H; to verrey U. <I>foule</I>] wicked H.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Schal no sonenday &thorn;is seuen &yogh;er &middot; (bote seknesse hit make),<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is</I>] be &thorn;is TU. <I>&yogh;er</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="232">&THORN;at I ne schal do me ar day &middot; to &thorn;e d[e]ore churche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>do me ar</I>] euery H. <I>to&mdash;deore</I>] to the dere T; rise erly to H; to &thorn;e parische U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And here Matins and Masse &middot; as I a Monk were.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Matins&mdash;Masse</I>] masse &amp; matynes TH. <I>as&mdash;Monk</I>] a monk as I H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Schal non ale after mete &middot; holde me &thorn;ennes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>non ale</I>] no riot H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Til ichaue Euensong herd &middot; I beo-hote to &thorn;e Rode.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>beohote to</I>] behote TU; swere by H.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="65, A-text"></L>
<L>And &yogh;it I-chulle &yogh;elden a&yogh;eyn &middot; &yogh;if I so muche haue,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ichulle &yogh;elden</I>] wile I &yogh;elde T; y wold &yogh;elde H; y wol &yogh;elde U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="237">Al &thorn;at I wikkedliche won &middot; se&thorn;&thorn;e I wit hade.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Al</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;auh my lyflode lakke &middot; letten I nulle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And &thorn;auh</I>] &thorn;ei&yogh; T. <I>my&mdash;lakke</I>] lyflode me faile U. <I>nulle</I>] ne wolle U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at vche mon schal habben his &middot; er ich henne wende:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vche</I>] euery HU; iche A T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="240">And with &thorn;e Residue and &thorn;e remenaunt &middot; (bi &thorn;e Rode of Chester!)</L>
<L>I schal seche seynt Treu&thorn;e &middot; er I seo Rome!"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seynt</I>] TU <I>omit. seo</I>] seke T; se H; see U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Robert &yogh;e Robbour &middot; on <I>Reddite</I> he lokede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on&mdash;he</I>] rufulliche H. <I>he</I>] TU <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for &thorn;er nas not Wher-with &middot; he wepte ful sore.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And&mdash;wherwith</I>] for &thorn;at he was wicked H. <I>ful</I>] swi&thorn;e THU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="244">But &yogh;it &thorn;e sunfol schrewe &middot; seide to him-seluen:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>But &yogh;it</I>] And &yogh;et TU; But H.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Crist, &thorn;at vppon Caluarie &middot; on &thorn;e Cros di&yogh;edest,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vppon</I>] on THU. <I>on</I>] vpon TH. <I>cros</I>] rode T. <I>di&yogh;edest</I>] deide HU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;o Dismas my bro&thorn;er &middot; bi-sou&yogh;te &thorn;e of grace,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] hym U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And heddest Merci of &thorn;at mon &middot; for <I>Memento</I> sake,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] And &thorn;ou TU; as &thorn;ou H. <I>of</I>] on THU. <I>memento</I>] memen|to-is TH.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;i wille wor&thorn; vppon me &middot; as Ich haue wel deseruet<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wor&thorn;</I>] werche TU. <I>as</I>] for H. <I>wel</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="249">To haue helle for euere &middot; &yogh;if &thorn;at hope neore.</L>
<L>So rewe on me, Robert &middot; &thorn;at no Red haue,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>me</I>] &thorn;is TU. <I>no Red haue</I>] red non ne haui&thorn; T; no reed ne haue H; reed non haue&thorn; U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne neuere weene to wynne &middot; for Craft &thorn;at I knowe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>weene</I>] weni&thorn; TU. <I>for&mdash;knowe</I>&middot;] wi&thorn; craft &thorn;at he knowi&thorn; TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="252">Bote for &thorn;i muchel Merci &middot; mitigacion I be-seche;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>muchel</I>] grete U. H <I>reads</I>, bote for &thorn;i mytigacion &middot; mercy y by-seche.</NOTE></L>
<L>Dampne me not on domes day &middot; for I dude so ille."<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>omits these lines</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] at TU. <I>for</I>] for &thorn;at TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Ak what fel of &thorn;is Feloun &middot; I con not feire schewe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>omits these lines</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fel</I>] befel TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>But wel Ich wot he wepte faste &middot; watur with his ei&yogh;en,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>But</I>] THU <I>omit. faste</I>] H <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="256">And knouhlechede his gult &middot; to Crist &yogh;it eft-sones,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to&mdash;&yogh;it</I>] &thorn;erto H; &yogh;it U.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000118.tif" N="66, A-text"></L>
<L>&THORN;at <I>Penitencia</I> is [pike &middot; he] schulde polissche newe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>V <I>reads</I>, &thorn;at Penitencia is prest &middot; schulde polissche him newe.</P><P><I>But this is probably wrong; cf</I>.</P><P>&thorn;at penitencia his pike &middot; he shulde pulsshe newe T;</P><P>&thorn;at penaunce his piked staf &middot; shulde be polischid al new H;</P><P>&thorn;at penitencia his pyke &middot; schulde pulsche newe U.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>And lepe with him ouerlond &middot; al his lyf tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>leep</I>] go H.</NOTE></L>
<L>For he ha&thorn; lei&yogh;en bi <I>latro</I> &middot; lucifers brother.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ha&thorn; lei&yogh;en</I>] hadde lei&yogh;e TU; hadde leyn H. <I>brother</I>] hyne T; Aunte U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="260">&para; A &thorn;ousent of Men &thorn;o &middot; &thorn;rongen to-geders,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A</I>] And T. <I>of&mdash;&thorn;o</I>] of men T; men H; men &amp; mo &thorn;o U. <I>&thorn;rongen</I>] &thorn;e wronge (!) T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Weopyng and weylyng &middot; for heore wikkede dedes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>weylyng</I>] wringing H. <I>heore&mdash;dedes</I>] here mysdedis H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Cri&yogh;inge vpward to Crist &middot; and to his clene moder<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Cri&yogh;inge</I>] Criede T; Cryden U. <I>clene</I>] dere T.</NOTE></L>
<L>To haue grace to seche seint treu&thorn;e &middot; god lene &thorn;ei so mote!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seint</I>] THU <I>omit. god&mdash;mote</I>] god lene &thorn;at hy moten T; so god lene &thorn;at &thorn;ei mote U.</NOTE>
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000119.tif" N="67, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS VI.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Title from</I> T; <I>also called</I> Passus Sextus <I>in</I> HUD.</NOTE>[<I>Passus Sextus de visione, vt prius</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>[NOw riden &thorn;is folk &middot; &amp; walken on fote<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>These two lines are in</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>to seche &thorn;at seint &middot; in selcou&thorn;e londis].<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>These two lines are in</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>BOte &thorn;er were fewe men so wys &middot; &thorn;at cou&thorn;e &thorn;e wei &thorn;ider,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>were</I>] was T. <I>men</I>] U <I>omits. &thorn;at&mdash;&thorn;ider</I>] &thorn;at &thorn;ei &thorn;ider cou&thorn;e T; &thorn;e wey &thorn;ider coude U; &thorn;at &thorn;e wey cou&thorn;en H.</NOTE></L>
<L>BOte bustelyng for&thorn; as bestes &middot; ouer valeyes and hulles,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bustelyng</I>] blustrid T; blustren U; bolstride H. <I>for&thorn; as</I>] as blynd H. <I>and</I>] or U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="5">[for while &thorn;ei wente here owen wille &middot; &thorn;ei wente alle amys].<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Til [hit] was late and longe &middot; &thorn;at &thorn;ei a Leod metten,<NOTE PLACE="foot">(<I>hit</I>) <I>was</I>] <I>So in</I> H; TU <I>omit;</I> V <I>omits</I> hit. <I>leod</I>] lede TU; man H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Apparayled as a Palmere &middot; In pilgrimes wedes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Palmere</I>] paynym TU. <I>wedes</I>] wyse THU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">He bar a bordun I-bounde &middot; wi&thorn; a brod lyste,<NOTE PLACE="foot">He bar a burdoun in his hond &middot; bounde wi&thorn; a lyste H.</NOTE></L>
<L>In A we&thorn;e-bondes wyse &middot; I-wri&thorn;en aboute.<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits. we&thorn;ebondes</I>] wode|byndes H; way wendis T. <I>Iwri&thorn;en</I>] he bond hym T.</NOTE></L>
<L>A Bagge and a Bolle &middot; he bar bi his syde;</L>
<L>An hundred of ampolles &middot; on his hat seeten,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>seeten</I>] seten THU.</P><P>OBS. <I>In this l.</I> H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>has</I> apples (!) <I>for</I> ampolles.</P></NOTE></L>
<L N="12">Signes of Synay &middot; and Schelles of Galys;</L>
<L>Moni Cros on his cloke &middot; and kei&yogh;es of Rome,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Moni cros on</I>] And many crouch in T; &amp; many crosses on H; And many a cros on U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;e vernicle bi-fore &middot; for men schulde him knowe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bifore</I>] to-fore H; hym by|forn U. <I>hym knowe</I>] y-knowe H; knowe T</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000120.tif" N="68, A-text"></L>
<L>And seo be his signes &middot; whom he souht hedde.<MILESTONE N="398b:1" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="16">&para; &THORN;is Folk fraynede him feire &middot; from whenne &thorn;at he coome?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>Expanded in</I> U <I>into two lines;</I></P><P>&thorn;is folk frayneth him faire &middot; for hym &thorn;at hym made,</P><P>Fro whennes &thorn;at be come &middot; &amp; whiderward he schulde. <I>from whenne</I>] whenis T.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>"From Synay," he seide, &middot; "and from the Sepulcre;</L>
<L>From Bethleem and Babiloyne &middot; I haue ben in bo&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">at bedlem &amp; at babilon &middot; haue y ben also H. <I>From&mdash;Babiloyne</I>] At bedlem (bethlem U) at babiloyne TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Ynde and in Assye &middot; and in mony o&thorn;er places.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In&mdash;Assye</I>] In Armonye, in Alisaundre THU. <I>and</I>] TU <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="20">&YOGH;e mouwe seo be my Signes &middot; &thorn;at sitte&thorn; on myn hat,</L>
<L>&THORN;at I haue walked ful wyde &middot; In weete and in druye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ful</I>] wel T; U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And souht goode seyntes &middot; for my soule hele."</L>
<L>&para; "Knowest &thorn;ou ouht A Corseynt &middot; Men calle&thorn; Seynt Treu&thorn;e?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ouht&mdash;corseynt</I>] ou&yogh;t a cor|seint, quod &thorn;ei TU; a seint, quo&thorn; &thorn;ei H. <I>Men&mdash;seynt</I>] &thorn;at men callen THU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">Const &thorn;ou wissen vs &thorn;e wey &middot; wher &thorn;at he dwelle&thorn;?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wissen</I>] teche H. <I>he</I>] wy T. <I>dwelle&thorn;</I>] walke&thorn; H.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"Nay, so God glade me!" &middot; seide &thorn;e gome &thorn;enne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>God&mdash;me</I>] god mote me helpe T; god me helpe H; me god helpe U. <I>gome</I>] man T; pilgrym H.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Sauh I neuere Palmere &middot; with pyk ne with schrippe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sauh I</I>] I sau&yogh; TH. <I>pyk&mdash;schrippe</I>] scrip ne wi&thorn; pyk H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Such a seint seche &middot; bote now in &thorn;is place."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Such&mdash;seche</I>] Axen aftir hym TU; aske after seint treu&thorn;e H. <I>bote</I>] er T; eer &thorn;an U.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Peter!" quod a Plou&yogh;-Mon &middot; and putte for&thorn; his hed,</L>
<L>"I knowe him as kuyndeliche &middot; as Clerk do&thorn; his bokes;</L>
<L N="30">Clene Concience and wit &middot; [kende] me to his place,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Clene</I>] kynde H. <I>and wit</I>] H <I>omits</I>. [<I>kende</I>] <I>So in</I> TU; VH <I>read</I> tau&yogh;te. <I>to</I>] ri&yogh;t to H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And dude enseure me se&thorn;&thorn;e &middot; to serue him for euere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>enseure&mdash;se&thorn;&thorn;e</I>] me to sure hym TU; me assure H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Bo&thorn;e to sowen and to setten &middot; while I swynke mihte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to&mdash;setten</I>] sowe his seed T; now and sithe U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="33">I haue ben his felawe &middot; &thorn;is fiftene wynter;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>felawe</I>] folowere TU; holdere H. <I>&thorn;is fiftene</I>] al &thorn;is fourty TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e I-sowed his seed &middot; and suwed his beestes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>suwed</I>] kepid U; folewid H.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="69, A-text"></L>
<L>And eke I-kept his Corn &middot; I-caried hit to house,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eke</I>] TH <I>omit. I-caried</I>] &amp; cariede THU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">I-dyket and I-doluen &middot; I-don what he hihte,<NOTE PLACE="foot">I haue dichid &amp; doluen &middot; &amp; do what he bad H. <I>Idon</I>] and do THU.</NOTE></L>
<L>With-Innen and withouten &middot; I-wayted his profyt;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I-wayted</I>] waytide T; to wayten U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er nis no laborer in &thorn;is leod &middot; &thorn;at he loue&thorn; more,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nis</I>] is H. <I>laborer</I>] laboure H. <I>&thorn;is leod</I>] his lordsshipe TU; lordschip H. <I>he loue&thorn; more</I>] he loui&thorn; betere T; hym like&thorn; betere U.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;auh I Sigge hit my-self &middot; I serue him to paye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>paye</I>] plese U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; I haue myn hure of him wel &middot; and o&thorn;erwhile more;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I</I>] And T. <I>wel</I>] TH <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="41">He is &thorn;e presteste payere &middot; &thorn;at por&eacute; men habbe&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>presteste</I>] rediest H. <I>habbe&thorn;</I>] knowen TU; knowi&thorn; H.</NOTE></L>
<L>He with-halt non hyne his huire &middot; &thorn;at he hit na&thorn; at euen.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>with-halt</I>] ne halt TU. <I>hit na&thorn;</I>] ne ha&thorn; it TU. H <I>reads</I>, he with-holdi&thorn; no mannys huyre &middot; he paie&thorn; hem at euen.</NOTE></L>
<L>He is as louh as A lomb &middot; louelich of speche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>louelich</I>] &amp; loueliche TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">And &yogh;if &yogh;e wolle&thorn; I-wite &middot; wher &thorn;at he dwelle&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And &yogh;if</I>] &yogh;if &thorn;at H. <I>&yogh;e&mdash;I|wite</I>] &thorn;at &yogh;e wille wite U. <I>he</I>] wy T.</NOTE></L>
<L>I wol wissen ow &thorn;e wey &middot; hom to his place."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>I shal wisse &yogh;ow wel &middot; &thorn;e ri&yogh;t way to his place T;</P><P>I shal teche &yogh;ou ful ri&yogh;t &middot; home to his house H;</P><P>I schal wisse &yogh;ow &thorn;e wey &middot; right to his place U.</P></NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"YE, leue pers," quod &thorn;is palmers &middot; and profreden him huire.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is palmers</I>] &thorn;e pilgrimes THU.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Nai, bi &thorn;e peril of my soule," quod pers &middot; and bigon to swere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nai</I>] H <I>om. pers</I>] he H. <I>bigon to</I>] gan to T; gan for to U; fast he dide H.</NOTE></L>
<L>"I nolde fonge a fer&thorn;ing &middot; for seynt Thomas schrine!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fonge</I>] take H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="49">Treu&thorn;e wolde loue me &thorn;e lasse &middot; a gret while after!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Treu&thorn;e</I>] For treu&thorn;e TU. <I>lasse</I>] wers THU. <I>a&mdash;after</I>] a longe time aftir TU; a gret while here after H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Bote &yogh;e &thorn;at wende&thorn; to him &middot; &thorn;is is &thorn;e wei &thorn;ider:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wende&thorn;&mdash;him</I>] wilne&thorn; to wende TU; wole to hym wende H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;e mote go &thorn;orw mekenesse &middot; bo&thorn;e Mon and wyf,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mon&mdash;wyf</I>] men &amp; wyues TU. OBS. 52&mdash;Pass. VII. 1. 2. MS. H <I>has here lost a folio; the rest of the Passus is collated with</I> D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Til &yogh;e come in-to Concience &middot; &thorn;at crist knowe &thorn;e so&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>knowe</I>] wyte TUD.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000122.tif" N="70, A-text"></L>
<L N="53">&THORN;at &yogh;e loue&thorn; him leuere &middot; &thorn;en &thorn;e lyf in oure hertes,</L>
<L>And &thorn;enne oure neihebors next &middot; In none wyse apeire<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>apeire</I>] apeiri&thorn; T; to apeire UD.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;erweys &thorn;en &thorn;ou woldest &middot; men wrou&yogh;ten to &thorn;i-seluen.</L>
<L>&para; So Bouwe&thorn; for&thorn; bi a brok &middot; beo-boxum-of-speche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>So bouwe&thorn;</I>] And so bou&yogh; T; And so bowe&thorn; U; And so bowe D. <I>brok</I>] banke T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="57">[For&thorn; til &yogh;e fynde a forde &middot; &yogh;our-fadres-honoureth];<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> U; <I>also in</I> TD. <I>For&thorn; til</I>] For to T; For D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wade&thorn; in &thorn;at water &middot; wassche&thorn; ow wel &thorn;ere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Wadi&thorn;</I>] Wades U. <I>wasshe&thorn;&mdash;&thorn;ere</I>] &amp; wassche &yogh;ou &thorn;erynne U.</NOTE></L>
