<L>Ne no Beggere eten Bred &middot; &thorn;at Benes Inne coome,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Beggere</I>] lengere U. <I>eten</I>] ete no U. <I>Inne coome</I>] comen ynne U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="292">Bote Coket and Cler Matin &middot; an of clene whete;<MILESTONE N="399b:2" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I>] or TU. <I>an</I>] or TU; &amp; H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne non halfpeny Ale &middot; In none wyse drynke,<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>omits</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>none</I>] no T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote of &thorn;e Beste and &thorn;e Brouneste &middot; &thorn;at Brewesters sullen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>omits</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and &thorn;e</I>] and of U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Laborers &thorn;at haue no lond &middot; to liuen on Bote heore honden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>haue</I>] hadde U. <I>to&mdash;honden</I>] but lyue on here handis T; but lyue by hemsilue H; to lyue by but here handes U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="296">Deyne not to dyne a day &middot; niht-olde wortes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Deyne</I>] Deyne&thorn; T; Deygned U. <I>not</I>] H <I>om. dyne&mdash;day</I>] dynen wi&thorn; U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mai no peny Ale hem paye &middot; ne no pece of Bacun,</L>
<L>Bote hit weore Fresch Flesch &middot; or elles Fisch I-Fri&yogh;et,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hit weore</I>] &yogh;if it be T; it be UH. <I>Fresch</I>] rostid U. <I>elles</I>] T <I>om.;</I> fresch H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e chaud and pluschaud &middot; for chele of heore Mawe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bo&thorn;e</I>] And TU. <I>chele</I>] chil|lyng THU. <I>heore mawe</I>] his mawe T; here mawes H; here chekys U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Bote he beo heihliche I-huret &middot; elles wol he chide,<NOTE PLACE="foot">H <I>reads</I>, but &thorn;ei be hi&yogh;ely y-huyred, ellis wollen &thorn;ei chide. <I>he</I>] &yogh;if he T. <I>heihliche</I>] lyliche U (<I>wrong</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L N="301">&THORN;at he was werkmon I-wrou&yogh;t &middot; warie &thorn;e tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he was</I>] &thorn;ei were H. <I>Iwrou&yogh;t</I>] bycome H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Corse &yogh;erne &thorn;e kyng &middot; and al his Counseil aftur,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Corse &yogh;erne</I>] &thorn;anne curse T; curse H. <I>his</I>] &thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Suche lawes to loke &middot; laborers to chaste.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>chaste</I>] chastise T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="304">&para; Ac while hunger was Mayster heer &middot; wolde &thorn;er non chyde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">301&mdash;304. U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mayster heer</I>] here maister T <I>&thorn;er non</I>] &thorn;ei not H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne striue a&yogh;eyn &thorn;e statues &middot; so steorneliche he lokede.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>statues</I>] statut T; statutes UH. U <I>reads</I>, And stryue a&yogh;ens &thorn;e statutes &middot; and sternely loken.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="91, A-text"></L>
<L>&para; I warne &yogh;ou, alle werk-men &middot; winne&thorn; while &yogh;e mowe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>alle</I>] THU <I>omit. winne&thorn;</I>] werche&thorn; H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="307">Hunger hiderward a&yogh;eyn &middot; hi&yogh;e&thorn; him &yogh;eorne.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hunger</I>] For hungir THU. <I>a&yogh;eyn</I>] THU <I>om. hi&yogh;e&thorn;&mdash;&yogh;eorne</I>] hasti&thorn; hym faste T; hasti&thorn; ful fast H; hyeth hym faste U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; He wole a-wake &thorn;orw watur &middot; &thorn;e wastours alle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wole&mdash;watur</I>] shal awake &thorn;is water T; wol wade &thorn;ur&yogh; watris H; schal awake &yogh;our wele U. <I>&thorn;e</I>] his U; TH <I>om. alle</I>] to chaste THU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Er Fyue &yogh;er ben folfult &middot; such Famyn schal a-Ryse<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fyue</I>] fewe H. <I>schal</I>] wol H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;orw Flodes and foul weder &middot; Fruites schul fayle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>flodes</I>] flood T; tempestes U. <I>and</I>] o&thorn;er &thorn;oru&yogh; T. <I>weder</I>] wederis TU. <I>fruites</I>] flodis U. <I>fayle</I>] falle TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="311">And so sei&thorn; [Saturne] &middot; and sent vs to warne.<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>Saturne</I>] satourne T; saturne HU; V <I>has</I> Saturnes. <I>sent vs</I>] sente &yogh;ow T; sende &yogh;ow H; sendith &yogh;ow U.</NOTE>
</L>
</LG>

