<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000144.tif" N="92, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS VIII.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Title; from</I> T. <I>Also called</I> P. octavus <I>in</I> HUD.</NOTE>[<I>Passus Octauus de Visione, vt prius.</I>]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>TReu&thorn;e herde telle her-of &middot; And to Pers sende,</L>
<L>To taken his teeme &middot; and tilyen &thorn;e eor&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>tilyen&mdash;eor&thorn;e</I>] his er&thorn;e tilien T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And purchasede him a pardoun &middot; <I>A pena et a culpa</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>purchasede</I>] purchace TH; pur|chasen U. <I>a</I>] U <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="4">For him, and for his heires &middot; euer more aftur.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for his</I>] his U. <I>euer</I>] for euere T. <I>aftur</I>] &thorn;eraftir U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bad holden hem at hom &middot; and heren heore ley&yogh;es,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>holden hem</I>] hym holde hym THU. <I>heore ley&yogh;es</I>] his lai&yogh;es TU; here leies H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And al &thorn;at euere hulpen him &middot; to heren or to sowen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>al</I>] &thorn;o T. <I>euere</I>] THU <I>om. him</I>] T <I>om. or</I>] &amp; H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Or eny maner mester &middot; &thorn;at mihte Pers helpen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>or eny</I>] &amp; alle H. <I>maner</I>] maner of T. <I>mester</I>] myster men H. <I>mihte Pers</I>] piers myghte U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">Part in &thorn;at pardoun &middot; &thorn;e Pope ha&thorn; I-graunted.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>] of H. <I>&thorn;at</I>] &thorn;e T. <I>Igraunted</I>] hem grauntid TU.</NOTE></L>
