<L>And Rihtfuliche Rulen &middot; &thorn;e Reame and &thorn;e peple,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Rihtfulliche</I>] rewfulliche (!) T. <I>rulen&mdash;&thorn;e</I>] in reaum rewli&thorn; &thorn;e T; in here rewme rewlen here U; reulen &thorn;e rewmes &amp; &thorn;e H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Han pardoun &thorn;orw Purgatorie &middot; to passen ful sone,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ful</I>] wel TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">Wi&thorn; patriarkes in paradys &middot; to pleyen &thorn;er-aftur.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pleyen</I>] pleyen hem U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Busschops &thorn;at blessen &middot; and bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lawes cunnen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] TU <I>om. cunnen</I>] kenne TU; knowen H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Loke&thorn; on &thorn;at on lawe &middot; and lere&thorn; men &thorn;at o&thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at on</I>] &thorn;at o T; &thorn;e to U. <I>lere&thorn;</I>] lere T; leren H; lerne U. <I>&thorn;at o&thorn;er</I>] &thorn;e tothir U.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000145.tif" N="93, A-text"></L>
<L>And bere&thorn; hem bo&thorn;e on heore bac &middot; as heore baner schewe&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>baner schewe&thorn;</I>] dedis shewyn H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">And preche&thorn; heore persouns &middot; &thorn;e peril of sunne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>persouns</I>] paryschens U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hou heore schabbede schep &middot; schal heore wolle saue,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heore</I>] &thorn;at TU; &thorn;at here H. <I>schabbede</I>] shabbide TH; scabbide U. <I>schal</I>] schulde H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Han Pardoun with &thorn;e Apostles &middot; whon &thorn;ei passen hennes,</L>
<L>And atte day of dom &middot; with hem on deis setten.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And atte</I>] And at &thorn;e T; On &thorn;e U; at &thorn;e H. <I>with&mdash;deis</I>] at here deis to TU; on hi&yogh;e deis to H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20">&para; Marchau[n]s in &thorn;is Margin &middot; hedden mony &yogh;eres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is</I>] &thorn;e THU. <I>mony &yogh;eres</I>] &yogh;eris many H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote non <I>A pena et a culpa</I> &middot; &thorn;e pope nolde hem graunte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nolde hem</I>] wolde hym T; wolde U.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;ei holde&thorn; not heore haly-day &middot; as holy churche teche&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>holde&thorn;</I>] helde T. <I>heore haly|day</I>] here haly-dayes TH; &thorn;e haly|day U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for &thorn;ei sworen bi heore soule &middot;&mdash;"so God hem moste helpe!"&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sworen</I>] swere THU. <I>soule</I>] soulis H. <I>so</I>] &amp; so T. <I>hem moste</I>] muste hem TU; shulde hem H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">A&yogh;eyn heore clene Concience &middot; heore catel to sulle.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heore</I>] THU <I>om. catel</I>] ware U.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>BOte vndur his secre seal &middot; Treu&thorn;e sende a lettre,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sende</I>] sente hym T; sente U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Bad hem Bugge Boldely &middot; what hem best lykede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hem</I> (1) hym] T. <I>hem best</I>] &thorn;at hym T. <I>lykede</I>] like&thorn; TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And se&thorn;&thorn;en sullen hit a-&yogh;eyn &middot; And saue &thorn;e wynnynge,<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">And make <I>Meson deu &thorn;er</I>-with &middot; Meseyse to helpe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>make</I>] &thorn;e U (<I>wrong</I>). <I>meson deu</I>] mesonis deux T; mesoun dieux H. <I>meseyse</I>] myseises T; mesels H; &thorn;e myseyse U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And wikkede wones &middot; wihtly to amende;<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>reads</I>, Wightliche wikkide weyes &middot; for to don amende. <I>And&mdash;wones</I>] Wykkide weyes T; &amp; also wicked weies H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Beete Brugges a-Boute &middot; &thorn;at to-Broke were,<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits. Beete Brugges</I>] And bynde brugges T; &amp; bigge brigges H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Marie Maydens &middot; or Maken hem Nonnes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Marie</I>] &amp; marien H. <I>or</I>] also &amp; T; or ellis H. <I>nonnes</I>] wyues U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="32">&para; Pore widewes &thorn;at wolde beo &middot; none wyues aftur,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Wydewis &thorn;at wiln not be wyues &middot; helpe hem &thorn;er aftir T; &thorn;at pore wydewes wol ben &middot; and none wyues aftir U. <I>none</I>] no more H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Fynde suche heore foode &middot; for Godes loue of heuene;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Godes</I>] oure lordis THU.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000146.tif" N="94, A-text"></L>
<L>&para; Sette scolers to scole &middot; or to sum o&thorn;er craft,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sette</I>] &amp; sett HU. <I>to&mdash;craft</I>] summe skynes craftis T; to somme kynne crafte U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Rule Religion &middot; and Rente hem Betere;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Rule</I>] Releue T; Reule wel U; &amp; releue H. <I>Religion</I>] religiouse HU. <I>Rente&mdash;betere</I>] rede hem &thorn;e beste U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">"And I schal sende ow my-self &middot; seint Mihel myn Aungel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ow</I>] &yogh;ow UH; T <I>om. myself</I>] selue U. <I>Mihel</I>] Michel TU; my&yogh;hel H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at no deuel schal &yogh;ou dere &middot; whon &yogh;e dye schulle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whon&mdash;schulle</I>] di&yogh;e whan &yogh;e di&yogh;e TU; when &yogh;e be&thorn; dede H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I ne schal sende &yogh;or soules &middot; saaf in-to heuene,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at I</I>] for I H; &thorn;at he U. <I>ne</I>] H <I>om. &yogh;or soules</I>] his soule T. <I>saaf into</I>] sauely to H.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bi-foren &thorn;e Face of my Fader &middot; fourmen or seetes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] H <I>om. &thorn;e&mdash;Fader</I>] my fadir face U. <I>fourmen&mdash;seetes</I>] frely &yogh;ow sette H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="40">Vsure And Auarice &middot; and o&thorn;es I defende,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I</I>] y &yogh;ou H.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at no gile go with ou &middot; Bote &thorn;e grace of treu&thorn;e."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>grace of</I>] grai&thorn; T; grete HU.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Enne were Marchaundes Murie &middot; &thorn;ei wopen for Ioye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ei wopen</I>] many wepe T; &amp; wepten H; and wepyn U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &yogh;eeuen wille for his writynge &middot; wollene clo&thorn;es;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;eeuen</I>] &yogh;af TH. <I>wille</I>] william H. <I>wollene</I>] wel newe H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">For he Copiede &thorn;us heore Cause &middot; &thorn;ei couden him gret &thorn;onk.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] And for T. <I>he copiede</I>] to copie H. <I>heore cause</I>] here clause TU; &thorn;is clause H. <I>&thorn;ei&mdash;&thorn;onk</I>] &thorn;ei &yogh;eue hym gret mede T; &thorn;ei cou&thorn;e hym gret &thorn;ank H; cowde hym gret mede U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Men of lawe hedden lest &middot; for heo beo&thorn; [lo&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Men</I>] And men U. <I>hedden lest</I>] were laft oute H; &thorn;ei haddyn lest U. <I>heo&mdash;lo&thorn;</I>] lewid &thorn;ei ben alle T; &thorn;ey be&thorn; lo&thorn; H; lettrid &thorn;ei ben alle U; heo beo&thorn; lettred alle V.</NOTE></L>
<L>To mote for mene men &middot; but &yogh;if &thorn;ei hadde money;]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>This line, and the word</I> lo&thorn; <I>pre|ceding, are from</I> H. <I>The other MSS. omit it, and are hardly intelligible</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>So sei&thorn; &thorn;e sauter &middot; and sapience bo&thorn;e,<Q><I>Super Innocentes munera non Accipiunt. A Regibus</I> [<I>et principibus erit merces</I> (<I>eorum</I>).]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>So</I>] For so T; as H; And so U. <I>sei&thorn;</I>] <I>in</I> H <I>follows</I> sauter. <I>and</I>] &amp; &thorn;e H. <I>Innocentes</I>] innocentem TU. <I>Accipiunt</I>] accipies TU. <I>Regibus</I>] V <I>has</I> Regibus, &amp;c.; T <I>has down to</I> principibus; U <I>down to</I> erit; eorum <I>I have supplied</I>. H <I>quotes loosely</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of [princes] and Prelatus &middot; heor pencion schulde aryse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>princes</I> THU] V <I>has</I> Parisches (<I>wrong</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L N="49">And of &thorn;e pore peple &middot; no penewor&thorn; to take.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] no TU. <I>penewor&thorn;</I>] peny|wor&thorn; HU; peny T.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="95, A-text"></L>
<L>&para; Ac he &thorn;at spende&thorn; his speche &middot; and speke&thorn; for &thorn;e pore<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ac</I>] For U; but H. <I>pore</I>] pore peple U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at is Innocent and neodi &middot; and no mon ha&thorn; apeyret,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>&mdash;<I>neodi</I>] Also for an Inno|cent H; &thorn;at innocentis ben and nedy U. <I>and</I>] &thorn;at HU. <I>ha&thorn; apeyret</I>] apeiri&thorn; TH; hem apeire U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">Cumforte&thorn; him in his caas &middot; Coueite&thorn; not his goodes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>him</I>] hem U. <I>his caas</I>] &thorn;at cas TH; &thorn;at caas U. <I>his</I>] here HU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote for vr lordes loue &middot; lawe for him schewe&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>loue</I>] loue of heuen H. <I>him</I>] hem HU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Schal no deuel at his de&thorn;-day &middot; deren him wor&thorn; a Myte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wor&thorn;</I>] TU <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at he ne wor&thorn; siker saaf &middot; and so sei&thorn; &thorn;e psauter,<Q>[<I>Qui facit hec, non mouebitur in eternum</I>.]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>siker saaf</I>] saufe sykirly T; sikerly sauf U. [<I>Qui</I>, &amp;c.] <I>In</I> H <I>only</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Ac to bugge water, ne wynt &middot; [ne] wit, (is &thorn;e &thorn;ridde),<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ne wynt</I>] ne wynd T; or wind H; wynd U. [<I>ne</I>] <I>Supplied from</I> T; or H; V <I>om</I>. U <I>reads</I>, Ac to bigge water, wynd or wit &middot; is ydel, y rede (<I>which gives the sense</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L N="57">Nolde neuer holy writ &middot; God wot &thorn;e so&thorn;e!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nolde</I>] Ne wolde THU. <I>writ</I>] cherche U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;eos &thorn;reo for &thorn;ralles &middot; beo &thorn;riuen a-mong vs alle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;riuen</I>] &thorn;rowe T; throwen U; y-&yogh;euen H. <I>among</I>] H <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>To waxen or to wonien &middot; whe&thorn;er God lyke&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>or</I>&mdash;<I>wonien</I>] &amp; wanyen T; or to wanye H; and wanyn U. <I>whe&thorn;er</I>] where &thorn;at TU; whe&thorn;er &thorn;at H.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">His pardoun In purgatorie &middot; is petit, I trouwe,<MILESTONE N="400a:1" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is petit</I>] ful litel is H; wel litel is TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at eny Meede of mene Men &middot; for Motynge receyue&thorn;.</L>
<L>&para; &YOGH;e Legistres and lawyers &middot; &yogh;e witen wher I ly&yogh;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lawyers</I>] lawisteris T. <I>&yogh;e</I>] T <I>om. wher</I>] &yogh;if TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;e &yogh;e seon &thorn;at hit is so &middot; serue&thorn; to &thorn;e Beste.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>&mdash;<I>so</I>] it is &thorn;us TU. <I>serue&thorn;</I>] sewi&thorn; T; sueth U.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="64">Libbinde Laborers &middot; &thorn;at libben bi heore hondes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Libbinde</I>] Alle libbyng T; Alle lyuynge HU. <I>libben</I>] lyuen THU.</NOTE></L>
