<L N="147">Falden bi-fore his Feet &middot; and heileden him alle.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In</I> T <I>and</I> U <I>only</I> two <I>lines</I>. And Iosep mette merueillously &middot; how &thorn;e mone &amp; &thorn;e sonne And &thorn;e en|leuene sterris &middot; halsiden hym alle T; And Ioseph mette merueilousliche &middot; how &thorn;e mone &amp; &thorn;e sonne And seuene sterres &middot; hailsede hym al abowtyn U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "<I>Beu fiz</I>, quod his Fader &middot; for defaute we schulle,</L>
<L>I my-self, and my sones &middot; seche &thorn;e for neode."</L>
<L>&para; Hit fel as &thorn;e Fader seide &middot; In Pharaones tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fel</I>] befel TU. <I>&thorn;e</I>] his TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;er Ioseph was Iustise &middot; Egipte to kepen.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;er</I>] &thorn;at TU. <I>Egipte</I>] al egipte U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="152">&para; Al &thorn;is make&thorn; me &middot; on Metels to &thorn;enken<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Transposed in</I> U.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>me</I>] me mochil U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mony tyme at Midniht &middot; whon [men] schulde slepe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>me</I>] me mochil U.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Mony tyme</I>] Manye tymes T. [<I>men</I>] T; VU <I>have</I> I.</NOTE></L>
<L>On Pers &thorn;e plouh-mon &middot; and whuch a pardoun he hedde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and&mdash;a</I>] whiche a T; &amp; whiche a U. <I>hedde</I>] haui&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And hou &thorn;e preost inpugnede hit &middot; al bi pure Resoun,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bi pure</I>] before T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="156">And diuinede &thorn;at Dowel &middot; Indulgence passede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>diuinede</I>] he leuide T. <I>pas|sede</I>] passi&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bienals and Trienals &middot; and Busschopes lettres
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="101, A-text"></L>
<L>Dowel on Domesday &middot; Is digneliche I-preiset,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on Domesday</I>] at &thorn;e day of dome TU. <I>digneliche</I>] ferfor&thorn;liche U. <I>I-preiset</I>] vndirfongen TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>He passe&thorn; al &thorn;e pardouns &middot; of seint Petrus churche.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>pardouns</I>] pardoun TU. <I>of</I>] at T. <I>churche</I>] chirche at rome U.</P><P>OBS. U <I>here inserts the Latin line</I>, Quodcunque, &amp;c.; <I>see</I> l. 162.</P></NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="160">Now ha&thorn; &thorn;e pope pouwer &middot; pardoun to graunte,</L>
<L>&THORN;e peple with-oute penaunce &middot; to passe to Ioye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to&mdash;Ioye</I>] a pena &amp; a culpa T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;is is a lef of vre bileeue &middot; as lettret men vs teche&thorn;,<Q><I>Quodcunque ligaueris super terram, erit ligatum et in celis</I>.</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a lef</I>] &thorn;e lif T; a leef U. <I>teche&thorn;</I>] shewi&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="163">And so bileeue I lelly &middot; (vr lord forbeode hit elles!)<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>so&mdash;lelly</I>] so I leue lelly T; y byleue it wel U. <I>vr</I>] TU <I>omit. hit</I>] T <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at pardoun and penaunce &middot; and preyers don sauen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>don sauen</I>] do salue T; to|gidres Mown saue U, (<I>the last two words being in</I> l. 165.)</NOTE></L>
<L>Soules &thorn;at han sunget &middot; seuen si&thorn;es dedlich.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sunget</I>] ysynned T; synned U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Bote trustene to Trienals &middot; treuly me &thorn;inke&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote&mdash;to</I>] And to triste on &thorn;is T; Ac to traste on &thorn;ese U. <I>treuly</I>] certes U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="167">Is not so syker for &thorn;e soule &middot; sertes, as do-wel.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Is</I>] It is T. <I>sertes</I>] trewly U (<I>see</I> l. 166). <I>as</I>] as is TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; For-&thorn;i I rede &yogh;ow Renkes &middot; &thorn;at Riche ben on eor&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For&thorn;i&mdash;Renkes</I>] &thorn;erfore y rede &thorn;at lordes U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vppon trust of oure tresour &middot; Trienals to haue,</L>
<L>Beo &yogh;e neuer &thorn;e Baldore &middot; to Breke &thorn;e ten hestes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Beo &yogh;e</I>] Be &thorn;ou UT.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; And nomeliche, &yogh;e Meires &middot; and &yogh;e Maister Iuges,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Meires&mdash;Iuges</I>] maistris, as meiris &amp; iuggis T; maistres, &thorn;at men &thorn;at Iugge&yogh; holden U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="172">&THORN;at han &thorn;e wel&thorn;e of &thorn;is world &middot; for wyse men ben holden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at&mdash;for</I>] &thorn;at han &thorn;e world at wille &amp; T; &thorn;ei to haue welthe of &thorn;is world U.</NOTE></L>
<L>To purchasen pardoun &middot; and &thorn;e popes Bulles.<NOTE PLACE="foot">T <I>omits this line. To</I>] For to U.</NOTE></L>
<L>At &thorn;e dredful day of dom &middot; &thorn;er dede schullen a-rysen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>day&mdash;dom</I>] dom day T. <I>&thorn;er</I>] whanne &thorn;e T; whan U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And comen alle bi-fore crist &middot; and a-Countes &yogh;elden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>alle</I>] T <I>omits. and acountes</I>] acountes to TU.</P><P>OBS. U <I>omits to end of Passus, leav|ing a small blank space</I>.</P></NOTE></L>
<L N="176">How &thorn;ou laddest &thorn;i lyf &middot; and his lawe keptest,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lyf</I>] life here T.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000154.tif" N="102, A-text"></L>
<L>What &thorn;ou dudest day bi day &middot; &thorn;e Doom &thorn;e wol rehersen;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>day&mdash;day</I>] day T (<I>by mistake</I>). <I>&thorn;e wol</I>] wile T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; A powhe ful of pardoun &thorn;er &middot; with Prouincials lettres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>powhe ful</I>] pokeful T. <I>with</I>] ne &thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="179">&THORN;auh &thorn;ou be founden in Fraternite &middot; a-mong &thorn;e foure Ordres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>] in &thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And habbe Indulgence I-doubled &middot; bote Dowel &thorn;e helpe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I doubled</I>] double-fold T.</NOTE></L>
<L>I nolde &yogh;eue for &thorn;i pardoun &middot; one pye hele!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nolde</I>] ne wolde T. <I>pardoun</I>] patent T.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>FOr&thorn;i I counseile alle cristene &middot; to crie crist merci,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to&mdash;crist</I>] cri&yogh;e god T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Marie his Moder &middot; to beo mene bi-twene,</L>
<L N="184">&THORN;at God &yogh;iue vs grace &middot; er we gon hennes,</L>
<L>Such werkes to worche &middot; while &thorn;at we ben here,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>while &thorn;at</I>] whiles T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at aftur vr de&thorn; day &middot; Dowel reherce,</L>
<L>&THORN;at atte day of dom &middot; we duden as he us hi&yogh;te.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>atte</I>] at &thorn;e T. <I>us</I>] T <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<TRAILER>[<I>Explicit hic visio</I> willelmi <I>de Petro de Plou&yogh;man. Eciam Incipit Vita de do-wel, do-bet, &amp; do|best</I>, secundum <I>wyt &amp;</I> resoun.]<NOTE PLACE="foot"> [<I>Explicit, &amp;c</I>.] <I>From</I> T; <I>so also</I> UH<SUB>2</SUB>D; <I>see</I> Critical Notes <I>and</I> Preface.</NOTE>
