<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000155.tif" N="103, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS IX.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>Incipit hic, &amp;c. <I>This is the only title that occurs in</I> V. <I>The large initial &thorn; is omitted by mistake, and a blank space left for it</I>.</P><P>OBS. H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>is collated with the rest to the end of the volume</I>.</P></NOTE>Incipit hic Dowel, Dobet, and Dobest.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&para; [&THORN;]us I-Robed in Russet &middot; Romed I a-boute<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Romed I</I>] I rombide T; y romyd al U; I rome H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Al a somer sesoun &middot; For to seche Dowel,</L>
<L>And [fraynide] ful ofte &middot; of [folk] &thorn;at I mette<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>fraynide</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>; y frayned U] askede V; <I>see l.</I> 5. [<I>folk</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] Men V; <I>see l.</I> 5.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">[&YOGH;if any wi&yogh;t wiste &middot; where do-wel was at Inne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> T; <I>also in</I> UH<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And what man he mi&yogh;te be &middot; of many man I askide].<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> T; <I>also in</I> UH<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>omits</I>.</NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he</I>] it U. <I>askide</I>] frayned U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Was neuer wiht as I wente &middot; &thorn;at me wisse cou&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wente</I>] wene TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wher &thorn;is ladde loggede &middot; Lasse ne more;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>loggede</I>] lengide TH<SUB>2</SUB>; lengith U. <I>Lasse ne more</I>] &thorn;e lesse ne &thorn;e more TH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">&para; Til hit fel on a Friday &middot; twei Freres I mette,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fel</I>] befel T; byfel U; befil H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Maistres of &thorn;e Menours &middot; Men of grete wittes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wittes</I>] wyt T; witte UH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich heilede hem hendeli &middot; as Ich hedde I-leorned,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heilede</I>] hailside TU; halside H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And preiede hem, par Charite &middot; er &thorn;ei [passede furre,]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>par</I>] for U. [<I>passede furre</I>] furre passede V; passide fer&thorn;ere TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">"&YOGH;if &thorn;ei [knewen any] Cuntre &middot; or Coostes a-boute<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>knewen any</I> T] knewe ony U; knewen ony H<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>has</I> knewe, <I>omit|ting</I> any.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wher &thorn;at Dowel dwelle&thorn; &middot; do me to wisse."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dwelle&thorn;</I>] dwellide TH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "Mari," quod [&thorn;e] Menour &middot; "A-mong vs he dwelle&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">V <I>has</I> a Menour; TH<SUB>2</SUB> &thorn;e maistris; U &thorn;ese maistres; <I>cf. ll.</I> 22, 24. <I>Among</I>] at hom wi&thorn; U; <I>see l.</I> 20.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000156.tif" N="104, A-text"></L>
<L>And euer ha&thorn;, as Ich hope &middot; and euer schal her-after."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>as</I>] TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">&para; "<I>Contra</I>," quod I as a Clerk &middot; and comsede to dis|puite,<Q>["<I>Sepcies in die cadit iustus;</I>]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot">V <I>omits the Latin quotation;</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>give it</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Seue si&thorn;es a day, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Bok &middot; sunge&thorn; &thorn;e rihtful mon;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a day</I>] on &thorn;e day U; TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit. sunge&thorn;</I>] falli&thorn; TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>mon</I>] TUH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And hose sunge&thorn;," I seide &middot; "certes, as me &thorn;inke&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I seide</I>] I sei&yogh;e TH<SUB>2</SUB>; he sei&thorn; U. <I>as</I>] TUH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Dowel and do vuele &middot; mowe not dwelle togedere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20"><I>Ergo</I>, he nis not alwey &middot; [at hom] among ow Freres,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>at hom</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>] a tom V; U <I>omits; see l.</I> 14.</NOTE></L>
<L>He is or while elles-wher &middot; to wisse &thorn;e peple."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>or while</I>] o&thorn;er while TH<SUB>2</SUB>; som tyme U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "I schal seie &thorn;e, my sone" &middot; seide &thorn;e Frere &thorn;enne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sone</I>] sawe U. <I>seide</I>] sei&thorn; U.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Hou seuen si&thorn;es &thorn;e sadde mon &middot; sunge&thorn; in a day;<NOTE PLACE="foot">How seuen sithes on &thorn;e day &middot; &thorn;e sadde man synnes U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">Bi [a forebisene]," seide &thorn;e frere &middot; "I schal &thorn;e feire schewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>a forebisene</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] ensaumple V. <I>seide</I>] quod TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Let bringe a Mon In A bot &middot; A-midde a Brod water,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a Brod</I>] the brode H<SUB>2</SUB></NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;e wint and &thorn;e watur &middot; and &thorn;e waggyng of &thorn;e Bot<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And &thorn;e wint</I>] &thorn;e wynd TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>waggyng&mdash;Bot</I>] wawes eke H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Make&thorn; &thorn;e Mon Mony tyme &middot; to stomble and to falle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e&mdash;tyme</I>] many tyme &thorn;e man U. <I>to&mdash;falle</I>] to falle &amp; to stande TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">(For stonde he neuere so stif &middot; he stumble&thorn; in &thorn;e wag|gyng);</L>
<L>And &yogh;it he is saaf and sound &middot; and so him bi-houe&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and sound</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &yogh;if he ne rise &thorn;e ra&thorn;er &middot; and rauhte to &thorn;e steorne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>rise</I>] arise TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>and&mdash;steorne</I>] &amp; ari&yogh;t sterede TH<SUB>2</SUB>; and raughte &thorn;e stere U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e wynt wolde with &thorn;e water &middot; &thorn;e Bot ouer-&thorn;rowe;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ouer&thorn;rowe</I>] ouertorne H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="32">&THORN;er weore &thorn;e Monnes lyf I-lost &middot; &thorn;orw [lachesse] of<MILESTONE N="400b:1" UNIT="folio"> himselue.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;orw</I>] for TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. [<I>lachesse</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] sleu&thorn;e V.</NOTE></L>
<L>Riht &thorn;us hit fare&thorn;," quod &thorn;e Frere &middot; "bi folk her on eor&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hit</I>] TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="105, A-text"></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e watur is liknet to &thorn;e world &middot; &thorn;at wonie&thorn; and waxe&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>liknet</I>] lyk U. <I>wonie&thorn;</I>] wani&thorn; T; wanyeth UH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>Also</I>, U <I>reads</I> wax|eth and wanyeth.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e goodes in &thorn;is world &middot; ben lyk &thorn;is grete wawes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in &thorn;is world</I>] of &thorn;is ground TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>ben&mdash;grete</I>] arn lyk to &thorn;e U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">Riht as wyndes and watres &middot; walewe&thorn; aboute.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Riht</I>] That H<SUB>2</SUB>T; And U. <I>wale|we&thorn;</I>] wawen TH<SUB>2</SUB>; wawes U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e Bot is liknet to &thorn;e Bodi &middot; &thorn;at Brutel is of kuynde;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>liknet</I>] like TU; liken H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>Brutel</I>] britel TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;orw &thorn;e fend and his Flesch &middot; and &thorn;e False world<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] That H<SUB>2</SUB>TU. <I>his</I>] &thorn;e TUH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="39">Sunge&thorn; &thorn;e sadde Mon &middot; seuen si&thorn;es in &thorn;e day.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>si&thorn;es</I>] tymes TH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>in</I>] on U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; But dedly sunne do&thorn; he not &middot; for Dowel him helpe&thorn;,</L>
<L>&THORN;at is charite &thorn;e Champion &middot; cheef help a&yogh;eyn sunne;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] And &thorn;at TH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>is</I>] H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>om. a&yogh;eyn sunne</I>] of alle U.</NOTE></L>
<L>For he streng&thorn;e&thorn; &thorn;e to stonde &middot; he sture&thorn; &thorn;i soule,<NOTE PLACE="foot">A&yogh;ens synne for to synne &middot; he stireth &thorn;e soule U (<I>corruptly</I>). <I>he sture&thorn;</I>] &amp; steri&thorn; TH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;au&yogh; &thorn;i bodi Bouwe &middot; as a Bot in &thorn;e Water,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a Bot</I>] bot do&thorn; TH<SUB>2</SUB>; a boot do&thorn; U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">Euer is &thorn;i soule saaf &middot; Bote &yogh;if &thorn;i-self wolle.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Euer</I>] Ay TUH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>&yogh;if</I>] &thorn;ou TH<SUB>2</SUB>; U <I>omits. wolle</I>] wilt TH<SUB>2</SUB>; wolt U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Folewe &thorn;i Flessches wil &middot; and &thorn;e fendes aftur,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fendes</I>] feend U; fende H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And do dedlich sunne &middot; and drenche &thorn;i-seluen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;i-seluen</I>] &thorn;i soule U.</NOTE></L>
<L>God wol soffre &thorn;e dye so &middot; for [&thorn;i-self hast &thorn;e maistrie]."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dye so</I>] to dei&yogh;e so TH<SUB>2</SUB>; to dey U. <I>&thorn;iself&mdash;maistrie</I>] <I>so in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>; &thorn;ou hast &thorn;e maistry U; &thorn;ou art &thorn;in owne Mayster V.</NOTE></L>
<L N="48">&para; "I haue no kynde knowyng," quod I &middot; "to conceyue &thorn;i wordes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>quod I</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
