</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Bote Mon is him Most lyk &middot; of Marke and of schap;</L>
<L N="33">For wi&thorn; word &thorn;at he warp &middot; woxen for&thorn; Beestes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wi&thorn;</I>] &thorn;oru&yogh; TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And alle &thorn;ing at his wille &middot; was wrou&yogh;t wi&thorn; a speche,<Q><I>Dixit et facta sunt;</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ing</I>] TUH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>om. dixit&mdash;sunt</I>] Faciamus hominem ad ymaginem et similitudinem nostram U; <I>see</I> l. 41.</NOTE></Q>
<PB REF="00000164.tif" N="112, A-text"></L>
<L>Saue Mon &thorn;at he Made &middot; Ymage to him-seluen,</L>
