</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Orw miht of his Maieste &middot; Mon was I-maket,<Q>[<I>Faciamus hominem ad ymaginem et similitudi|nem nostram</I>.]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>his</I>] &thorn;e TU. <I>Mon</I>] whan (!) U. Faciamus, &amp;c.] <I>From</I> U <I>above, at</I> l. 34; TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>insert it here, but omit</I> et similitudinem.</NOTE></L>
<L>Inwit and alle wittes &middot; ben closet &thorn;er-Inne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ben closet</I>] enclosid ben T; bien I-closid H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>For loue of &thorn;at ladi &middot; &thorn;at lyf is I-nempnet;</L>
<L N="44">&THORN;at is <I>Anima</I> &thorn;at ouer al &middot; in &thorn;e Bodi wandure&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>] U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>But in &thorn;e herte is hire hom &middot; hi&yogh;est of alle;</L>
<L>Heo is lyf and ledere &middot; and a lemmon of heuene.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and a</I>] and U; a T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Inwit is &thorn;e help &middot; &thorn;at <I>Anima</I> desyre&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>help</I>] halle T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="48">After &thorn;e grace of God &middot; &thorn;e gretteste is Inwit.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e&mdash;Inwit</I>] Inwyt is &thorn;e grettest TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Inwit in &thorn;e hed is &middot; and helpe&thorn; &thorn;e soule,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and helpe&thorn;</I>] &amp; an help to T; an help to UH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;orw his connynge he [kepe&thorn;] &middot; <I>Caro et Anima</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he kepeth</I>] is kept TU; <I>hence the reading of</I> V, <I>viz</I>. he clepe&thorn;, <I>is a mere mistake for</I> he kepe&thorn;; <I>see</I> l. 16.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Rule and in Reson &middot; bote Recheles hit make.</L>
<L N="52">&para; He egge&thorn; &thorn;e [ei&yogh;e-siht &middot; and herynge] to goode,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>The readings are</I>,</P><P>He egge&thorn; &thorn;e i&thorn;e siht &middot; and Bringe&thorn; to goode V;</P><P>He (It H<SUB>2</SUB>) eggi&thorn; ei&yogh;e-si&yogh;t &middot; &amp; herynge to gode TH<SUB>2</SUB>;</P><P>He eggide eye to sighte &middot; and herynge to gode U.</P><P><I>In</I> V, i&thorn;e <I>is probably written for</I> iye <I>or</I> eiye.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>Of good speche and of cunnynge &middot; he is &thorn;e biginnere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Of</I>] Ofte H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>good&mdash;cunnynge</I>] speche &amp; of goynge U.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Monnes Brayn he is most &middot; and mihtiest to knowe,</L>
<L>&THORN;er he is Bremest &middot; But &yogh;if blod hit make.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he is</I>] is his bour TU. <I>&yogh;if</I>] hoot U.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="113, A-text"></L>
<L N="56">For whonne Blod is Bremore &thorn;en Brayn &middot; &thorn;en is Inwit I-bounde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bremore &thorn;en</I>] brent in U. <I>Inwit</I>] &thorn;e wit U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And eke wantoun and wylde &middot; withouten eny Resoun.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN &yogh;onge Fauntes and Fooles &middot; with hem Fayle&thorn; Inwit,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;onge</I>] U <I>om. with</I>] in U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And eke in [sottes] &thorn;ou miht seo &middot; &thorn;at sitte&thorn; atte Ale;<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>sottes</I>] UTH<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>has</I> wrecches. <I>atte ale</I>] at &thorn;e nale TU; at &thorn;e ale H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">&THORN;ei helde&thorn; Ale in heore hed &middot; til Inwit beo a-dreynt,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>helde&thorn;</I>] helde T; heeld U; holde H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>adreynt</I>] drenchit TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And [ben] Brayn-wode as Beestes &middot; so heore Blod waxe&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>ben</I>] <I>So in</I> TU; bien H<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>omits. Braynwode</I>] brayned U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;enne ha&thorn; &thorn;e Pouke pouwer &middot; Sire <I>Princeps huius mundi</I>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>princeps&mdash;mundi</I>] <I>omitted in</I> U; <I>see</I> note.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ouer suche Maner Men &middot; Miht in heore soules.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>men</I>] of men T. <I>in</I>] is in U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote In Fauntes ne in Fooles &middot; &thorn;e Fend ha&thorn; no miht<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ne in</I>] and U. <I>Fend</I>] deuil T. <I>miht</I>] wit U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="65">For no werk &thorn;at &thorn;ei worchen &middot; wikked or elles;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>no</I>] to U (<I>wrongly</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote &thorn;e Fadres and &thorn;e Frendes &middot; For Fau[n]tes schul be Blamet<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Faderes</I>] fadir TU. <I>Fauntes</I> TU] V <I>has</I> Fautes.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote &thorn;ei witen hem from wantounesse &middot; whil &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben &yogh;onge.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote</I>] But &yogh;if T. <I>witen</I>] wone U. <I>&yogh;onge</I>] &yogh;ou&thorn;e T (<I>sic</I>); &yogh;onge H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="68">&para; And &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben pore or Catelles &middot; to kepen hem from ille,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And &yogh;if</I>] And H<SUB>2</SUB>; ac if U. <I>&thorn;at</I>] TU <I>om. to</I>] and U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;enne is holy chirche a-signet &middot; to helpen hem and sauen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>asignet</I>] owynge T; awynge U.</NOTE></L>
<L>From Folyes, and Fynden hem &middot; til &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben wysore.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Fynden</I>] fende H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>&thorn;at&mdash;wysore</I>] &thorn;ei ben wise T. U <I>reads</I>, And for to fynde hem for&thorn; &middot; til &thorn;ei ben wisere.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Bote vche [wi&yogh;t] in &thorn;is world &middot; &thorn;at ha&thorn; wys vnder|stondinge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote</I>] And TU. [<I>wi&yogh;t</I> T; <I>wight</I> U] mon V. <I>&thorn;is</I>] &thorn;e U. <I>ha&thorn;</I>] H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omits by mistake</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Is Cheef souereyn [of] him-self &middot; his soule for to &yogh;eme,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>of</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>] ouer TU; V <I>omits. for to</I>] to TU.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000166.tif" N="114, A-text"></L>
<L N="73">And Cheuesschen him from charge &middot; whon he childhode passe&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cheuesschen</I>] cheuisshi&thorn; TU. <I>from</I>] for any TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saue him-self from sunne &middot; for so him bi-houe&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Saue</I>] To saue U. <I>bihoue&thorn;</I>] behouid H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
