</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="76">&THORN;Ene is Dowel a Duyk &middot; &thorn;at distruie&thorn; vices,<MILESTONE N="401a:1" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] and U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And saue&thorn; &thorn;e soule &middot; &thorn;at sunne ha&thorn; no miht<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>To Route ne to Reste &middot; ne to Rooten in &thorn;e herte;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>To</I>] Ne U. <I>to&mdash;&thorn;e</I>] roren in &thorn;in T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;at is drede of God &middot; for Dowel hit make&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for</I>] TU <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="80">Hit is biginnynge of goodnesse &middot; God for to drede;<NOTE PLACE="foot">And is &thorn;e begynnynge &middot; god for to doute U. <I>drede</I>] douten TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>[Salamon it seide &middot; for a so&thorn; tale],<Q><I>Innicium sapiencie, timor domini</I>.</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> T; <I>also in</I> UH<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>timor</I>] est timor T.</NOTE></L>
<L>For doute, Men do&thorn; &thorn;e Bet; &middot; drede is such a Mayster</L>
