<L>&THORN;ou miht leose &thorn;i louhnesse &middot; for a luitel pruyde.</L>
<L N="100">&para; I haue lerned hou lewede men &middot; han lered heore children,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lerned</I>] herd TU. <I>how</I>] &yogh;ou H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>lered</I>] lernid T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at selden Mose&thorn; &thorn;e Marbelston &middot; &thorn;at men ofte treden;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>&thorn;at selde men se&thorn; &thorn;e marbil&middot; &thorn;at men ofte dreden T; (<I>corrupt</I>);</P><P>&thorn;at seelde men seen &thorn;e marbil mose &middot; &thorn;at men ofte mouen U;</P><P>That selde men seth the marbul &middot; that ofte men tredith H<SUB>2</SUB>.</P></NOTE></L>
