<L N="206">Vn-Gracios to gete loue &middot; or eni good elles,</L>
<L>&para; Bote wandren as wolues &middot; and wasten &yogh;if &thorn;ei mouwen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">But wandri&thorn; &amp; wasti&thorn; &middot; what &thorn;at &thorn;ei mowe T.</NOTE></L>
<L>A-&yogh;eyn Dowel &thorn;ei don vuele &middot; and &thorn;e deuel plesen,</L>
<L>And aftur heore de&thorn; day &middot; schul dwelle wi&thorn; &thorn;e schrewe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e schrewe</I>] &thorn;e same T; &thorn;at same H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="210">Bute God &yogh;iue hem Grace &middot; heer to A-Mende.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bute</I>] But &yogh;if T. <I>hem</I>] hym T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;enne is Dowel to dreden &middot; and Dobet to suffren,</L>
<L>And so come&thorn; Dobest aboute &middot; And bringe&thorn; a-doun Modi,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>modi</I>] mody TH<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;at is wikkede wil &middot; &thorn;at Mony [werke] schende&thorn;."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>] H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omits</I>. [<I>werke</I> H<SUB>2</SUB>T] men V.</NOTE>
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000174.tif" N="122, A-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS XI.</HEAD>
<HEAD>[<I>Passus secundus de dowel, &amp;c</I>.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">Passus, &amp;c.] <I>so in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>. OBS. <I>The readings of</I> H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>are the same as those of</I> T, <I>except when specially given as different</I>.</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Enne hedde wit A wyf &middot; was hoten dam Studie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>was hoten</I>] &thorn;at hatte T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at [lene was of lich] &middot; and of louh chere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lene&mdash;lich</I>] <I>so in</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>has</I> euer was I-liche. <I>louh</I>] lo&thorn;ly T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Heo was wonderliche wro&thorn; &middot; &thorn;at wit me &thorn;us tauhte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>me &thorn;us</I>] so me H<SUB>2</SUB>; so T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">And al starinde Dam Studie &middot; steorneliche seide,<NOTE PLACE="foot">And sterneliche staringe &middot; dame studie seide T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "Wel artou witti," quod heo &middot; "wisdom to telle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>artou witti</I>] art &thorn;ou wys, wyt T. <I>wisdome</I>] any wisdomis T.</NOTE></L>
<L>To Fayturs or to Fooles &middot; &thorn;at Frentik ben of wittes!"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Fayturs</I>] flatereris T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Blamede him for his Beere &middot; And Bad him beo stille<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for his Beere</I>] bitterly T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">Wi&thorn; suche wyse wordes &middot; to wisse eny fooles.</L>
<L>&para; And seide, "<I>Noli mittere</I> &middot; Margeri perles<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Noli mittere</I>] <I>Nolite mittere</I>. man T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Among hogges &thorn;at han &middot; hawes at heore wille;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heore</I>] T <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ei don bot drauele &thorn;eron &middot; draf weore hem leuere</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;en al &thorn;e presciouse Peerles &middot; &thorn;at in paradys waxen.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>presciouse Peerles</I>] precious perrie T. <I>waxen</I>] wexi&thorn; T; wexit H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; I sigge hit bi &thorn;ulke," quod heo &middot; "&thorn;at bi heore werkes schewen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hit&mdash;&thorn;ulke</I>] be &thorn;o T. <I>bi&mdash;schewen</I>] shewen be here werkis T; schewen here werkis H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at hem weore leuere lond &middot; and lordschupe on eor&thorn;e,</L>
<L>Richesse, Rentes &middot; or Reste at heore wille<NOTE PLACE="foot">Or ricchesse or rentis &middot; &amp; reste at here wille T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">&THORN;en Al &thorn;e so&thorn; sawes &middot; &thorn;at Salamon seide euere.
<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="123, A-text"></L>
<L>&para; Wisdam and wit nou &middot; is not wor&thorn; a Russche</L>
<L>But hit beo [cardet] with Couetise &middot; as clo&thorn;ers do&thorn; heor wolle,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>cardet</I>] cardit TH<SUB>2</SUB>; carket V.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Conterfete&thorn; disseites &middot; and Conspiret wronges,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Conterfete&thorn;</I>] can construe &thorn;e T; <I>conspiret</I>] conspire T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20">And lede&thorn; for&thorn; A loueday &middot; to lette &thorn;e trewe&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lede&thorn;</I>] lede T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at suche craftes cunnen &middot; to counseil beo&thorn; I-clept,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to&mdash;Iclept</I>] ben yclepid to counseil T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And ben serued as syres &middot; &thorn;at serue&thorn; &thorn;e deuel.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] and H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Iob &thorn;e Ientel &middot; in his Ieestes seide,<Q><I>Quare via impiorum prosperatur, bene est omnibus qui praue et inique agunt?</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seide</I>] seide it T. <I>bene</I>] ve TU. <I>praue</I>] peruerse U. (<I>This quotation oc|curs in</I> U <I>elsewhere; see note to</I> Pass. X. l. 145.)</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">&para; Ac he &thorn;at holy writ ha&thorn; &middot; euer in his mou&thorn;e,<MILESTONE N="401b:1" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>holy&mdash;euer</I>] ha&thorn; holy writ ay T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And con tellen of Tobie &middot; And &thorn;e Twelue Apostles,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And &thorn;e</I>] &amp; of &thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And prechen of &thorn;e penaunce &middot; &thorn;at Pilatus wrouhte<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] Or T. <I>Pilatus</I>] pilatis T.</NOTE></L>
<L>To Iesu &thorn;e Ientil &middot; &thorn;at Iewes to-drowe</L>
<L N="28">On Cros vppon Caluarie &middot; as Clerkes vs telle&thorn;;&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>telle&thorn;</I>] techi&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Luytel is he loued or leten bi &middot; &thorn;at such a lessun Rede&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Rede&thorn;</I>] techi&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Or Daunseled or Drawen for&thorn; &middot; &thorn;is Disours witen &thorn;e so&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Daunseled</I>] dauntid T.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &yogh;if Harlotrie ne Holpe hem &thorn;e bet &middot; (haue God my soule!)<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e bet</I>] betere T. <I>soule</I>] trou&thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="32">More &thorn;en Musyk &middot; or Makyng of Crist,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Crist</I>] god almi&yogh;t T; god al|my&yogh;ty H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wolde neuer kyng ne kniht &middot; ne Canoun of Seynt poules</L>
<L>&YOGH;euen hem to heore &yogh;eres-&yogh;iue &middot; &thorn;e value of a grote!</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>BOte Munstralsye and Mur&thorn;e &middot; A-Mong Men is nou&thorn;e;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote</I>] T <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="36">Lecherie and losengrie &middot; and loseles tales,</L>
<L>And geten gold with grete o&thorn;es &middot; beo&thorn; gamus nou A dayes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And&mdash;with</I>] Glotonye &amp; T. <I>beo&thorn;</I>] &thorn;ise arn T.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000176.tif" N="124, A-text"></L>
<L>But &yogh;if &thorn;ei Carpen of Crist &middot; (&thorn;is Clerkes and &thorn;is lewede)</L>
<L>Atte Mete in heor Mur&thorn;e &middot; whon Munstrals beo&thorn; stille,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Atte&mdash;mur&thorn;e</I>] At &thorn;e mete &amp; at mur&thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="40">&para; &THORN;enne telle&thorn; &thorn;ei of &thorn;e Trinite &middot; hou two slowen &thorn;e &thorn;ridde,</L>
<L>And Bringe&thorn; for&thorn; Ballede Resouns &middot; tak Bernard to witnesse,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ballede&mdash;tak</I>] a ballid resoun &middot; toke T.</NOTE></L>
<L>And puyte&thorn; for&thorn; presumpciun &middot; to preue &thorn;e so&thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>puyte&thorn;</I>] putte T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;us &thorn;ei drauelen on heore deys &middot; &thorn;e Deite to knowe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>drauelen on</I>] dryuelen at T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">And deme&thorn; God in-to &thorn;e gorge &middot; whon heore Gottus follen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">And gnawen god in here &thorn;rote &middot; whanne here guttis fullen T.</NOTE></L>
<L>But Carful Mon may crien &middot; and clepen atte &yogh;ate<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>But&mdash;Mon</I>] Ac &thorn;e carful T. <I>clepen atte</I>] carpe at &thorn;e T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e of hungur and of &thorn;urst &middot; and for chele quake;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of</I>] for T. <I>of</I>] for T. <I>quake</I>] quaki&thorn; T.</NOTE></L>
<L>Nis no Mon him neih &middot; his nuy to Amende,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>Is non to nymen him In &middot; ne his anguyssh amende T; H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omits</I> him.</P><P>OBS. <I>Here collation with</I> U <I>recom|mences</I>.</P></NOTE></L>
<L N="48">Bote honesschen him as an hound &middot; and hoten him go &thorn;ennes!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>honesschen</I>] honysche U; hunsen T.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Luyte loue&thorn; he &thorn;at lord &middot; &thorn;at lene&thorn; him &thorn;at Blisse,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at blisse</I>] al &thorn;at blisse T.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;us parte&thorn; with &thorn;e pore &middot; A parcel whon him neode&thorn;.</L>
<L>Neore Merci In Mene Men &middot; More &thorn;en in Riche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Neore</I>] Ne were U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">Wi&thorn; Mony defauti Meeles &middot; Mihte &thorn;ei go to bedde.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Manye men meteles &middot; mi&yogh;te go to bedde T; Manye mendinaw[n]tes meteles &middot; my&yogh;te go to bedde U.</NOTE></L>
<L>God is muche in &thorn;e gorge &middot; of &thorn;eose grete Maystres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] his U. <I>gorge</I>] &thorn;rote T; gorge H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote A-Mong Mene Men &middot; his Merci and his werkes;<NOTE PLACE="foot">U <I>omits. mene</I>] TH<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omit</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And so sei&thorn; &thorn;e psauter &middot; sech hit In "<I>Memento</I>,"<Q><I>Ecce Audiuimus eam in effrata, inuenimus [eam] in campis silue</I>.</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sech</I>] seek U; se T. [<I>eam</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] eum V.</NOTE></L>
<L N="56">&para; Clerkes and kete men &middot; Carpen of God ofte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>kete</I>] kid T; kedde U; kyd H<SUB>2</SUB>. <I>ofte</I>] faste TU.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000177.tif" N="125, A-text"></L>
<L>And han him muche in heore Mou&thorn; &middot; bote Mene men in herte.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>him</I>] TU <I>omit;</I> H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>retains</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Freres and Faytors &middot; han founden suche questions<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>founden</I>] founden vp TU; fonden H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
<L>To plese with &thorn;is proude men &middot; se&thorn;&thorn;e pestilence tyme;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is</I>] TU <I>omit. se&thorn;&thorn;e</I>] si&thorn;en &thorn;e T; si&thorn; &thorn;e U.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">&THORN;ei de-Foulen vre Fey &middot; at Festes &thorn;er &thorn;ei sitten.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ei</I>] &thorn;at TU. <I>Fey</I>] false (!) T; feyth U. <I>festes</I>] &thorn;e feste T.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>For nou is vche Boye Bold &middot; Bro&thorn;el an o&thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bro&thorn;el&mdash;o&thorn;er</I>] &amp; he be riche TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>To talken of &thorn;e Trinite &middot; to beon holden A syre,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>talken</I>] tellen TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And fynde&thorn; for&thorn; fantasyes &middot; vr fei&thorn; to Apeyre;</L>
<L N="64">And eke de-Fame&thorn; &thorn;e Fader &middot; &thorn;at vs alle made,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eke defame&thorn;</I>] defame T; to de|fame U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And Craken a&yogh;eyn &thorn;e Clergie &middot; Crabbede wordes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>craken&mdash;&thorn;e</I>] carpide a&yogh;ens T; carpen of U.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; 'Whi wolde God vr saueour &middot; suffre such a worm<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>God</I>] TU <I>omit. worm</I>] worm in his blisse TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>In such a wrong wyse &middot; &thorn;e wommon to bi-gyle?<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at he gilide &thorn;e womman &middot; &amp; &thorn;e wy aftir T; &thorn;at begyles &thorn;e womman &middot; &amp; &thorn;e man after U.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e hir hosebonde and heo &middot; to helle &thorn;orw him wenten,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;oru&yogh; whiche a werke &amp; wille &middot; &thorn;ei wenten to helle TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="69">And heore seed for &thorn;at sunne &middot; &thorn;e same wo drien.'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] And alle TU. <I>&thorn;at</I>] here T. <I>drien</I>] suffride TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Suche Motyues &thorn;ei meuen &middot; &thorn;is Maistres in heor glorie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>motyues</I>] motifs T; motes U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And make&thorn; Men Misbileeue &middot; &thorn;at [musen on] heore wordes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>musen on</I> T] mousen on U; leeuen in V; H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>torn away</I>.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="72">But Austin &thorn;e Olde &middot; for alle suche preche&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>preche&thorn;</I>] prechide T; prechet U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for suche tale tellers &middot; such a teeme schewe&thorn;,<Q><I>Non plus sapere quam oportet sapere</I>.</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>schewe&thorn;</I>] shewide T. <I>Non</I>] Nolite U. <I>oportet</I>] V <I>really has</I> oporte&thorn;, <I>of course by mistake</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;is wilne&thorn; &yogh;e neuer to wite &middot; whi &thorn;at God wolde<NOTE PLACE="foot">That is to seyn ne wilne&thorn; neuere &middot; for to wyte why TU; <I>see next line, and</I> l. 81.</NOTE></L>
<L>Soffre Sathan &middot; his sed to bi-gyle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Soffre</I>] That god wold suffre TU.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000178.tif" N="126, A-text"></L>
<L N="76">&para; But leeue&thorn; on &thorn;at lore &middot; &thorn;at lere&thorn; holichirche,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Ac beleue lelly of lore &middot; of holy chirche T; And be-leef lely on &thorn;e lord &middot; of holy chyrche U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And preye him of pardoun &middot; and penaunce in &thorn;i lyue,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>him</I>] H<SUB>2</SUB> <I>omits. of</I>] of his U. <I>in</I>] be TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for his muchele Merci &middot; to amenden vs heere.</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;at wilne&thorn; [to wite &middot; &thorn;e] weyes of god Almihti,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>to wite &thorn;e</I> UTH<SUB>2</SUB>] two V; <I>see</I> ll. 73, 81, 88. <I>weyes</I>] werkes T.</NOTE></L>
<L>I wolde his e&yogh;e weore in his ers &middot; and his heele aftur;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>e&yogh;e were</I>] ei&yogh;en wern T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="81">&THORN;at euer eft Wilne&thorn; to wite &middot; whi &thorn;at God wolde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whi &thorn;at</I>] why T. <I>&thorn;at&mdash;wolde</I>] <I>Begins</I> l. 82 <I>in</I> U; <I>cf</I>. l. 74.</NOTE></L>
<L>Soffre Sathan &middot; his seed to bi-gyle,</L>
<L>Or Iudas &thorn;e Ieu&yogh; &middot; Iesu bi-traye;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Or</I>] Er T. <I>bitraye</I>] betrayede T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="84">Al was as he wolde &middot; lord, I-heried be &thorn;ou!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Iheried&mdash;&thorn;ou</I>] yworsshipid be &thorn;ou T; I-wyrchepid &thorn;ou be U.</NOTE></L>
<L>And al [wor&thorn;] as &thorn;ou wolt &middot; what so we tellen!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>al</I>] U <I>om</I>. [<I>wor&thorn;</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] beo V.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; And nou come&thorn; a Conioun &middot; and wolde cacchen of [my] wittes,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>my</I> TH<SUB>2</SUB>] me V.</NOTE></L>
<L>What is Dowel from Dobet! &middot; nou daffe mot he wor&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nou</I>] U <I>om. daffe</I>] defe TU.</NOTE></L>
<L N="88">[Si&thorn;en] he wilne&thorn; to wite &middot; whuche &thorn;ei ben alle!<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>Si&thorn;en</I> T] si&thorn;&thorn;e U; sithen H<SUB>2</SUB>; V <I>has</I> Sire.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote he liue in &thorn;e leste degre &middot; &thorn;at longe&thorn; to Dowel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote&mdash;degre</I>] But &yogh;if he lyue lely in &thorn;e last day U.</NOTE></L>
<L>I dar ben his borw &middot; &thorn;at Dobet nul he neuere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I</I>] For I U. <I>borw</I>] bolde boru&yogh; TU. <I>&thorn;at</I>] TU <I>omit. nul</I>] wile TU.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;au&yogh; Dobest drawe on him &middot; day aftur o&thorn;ur."</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="92">And whon &thorn;at wit was I-war &middot; hou his wyf tolde,</L>
<L>He bi-com so confoundet &middot; he cou&thorn;e not [mele],<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>He&mdash;confoundet</I>] He become&thorn; so confus T; He come so confuse U. [<I>mele</I> TUH<SUB>2</SUB>] medle V.</NOTE></L>
<L>And as doumbe as a dore &middot; drou&yogh; him asyde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And as</I>] Also T; And also U. <I>dore</I>] dore-nayl and H<SUB>2</SUB>.</NOTE></L>
