<L>And cartesadel &thorn;e comissarie &middot; owre carte shal he lede,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="25"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] oure O.</NOTE></L>
<L N="180">And fecchen vs vytailles &middot; at <I>fornicatores</I>.</L>
<L>&para; And maketh of lyer a longe carte &middot; to lede alle &thorn;ese othere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>maketh</I>] make C. <I>longe</I>] lang W; lange R. <I>&thorn;ese</I>] &thorn;ise WC; &thorn;es R.</NOTE></L>
<L>As Freres and faitours &middot; &thorn;at on here fete rennen."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Freres</I>] fobberes R. <I>faitours</I>] fautouris O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And thus fals and fauel &middot; fareth forth togideres,</L>
<L N="184">And Mede in &thorn;e myddes &middot; and alle &thorn;ise men after.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>men</I>] other CO.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; I haue no tome to telle &middot; &thorn;e taille &thorn;at hem folweth,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>tome</I>] toom O. <I>hem folweth</I>] hire folwed W.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of many maner man &middot; &thorn;at on &thorn;is molde libbeth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">W <I>omits</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac gyle was forgoer &middot; and gyed hem alle.</L>
<L N="188">&para; Sothenesse sei&yogh; hym wel &middot; and seide but a litel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hym</I>] hem WR. <I>a</I>] W <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And priked his palfrey &middot; and passed hem alle,</L>
<L>And come to &thorn;e kynges courte &middot; and conscience it tolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>come</I>] com WR.</NOTE></L>
<L>And conscience to &thorn;e kynge &middot; carped it after.</L>
<L N="192">&para; "Now by cryst," quod &thorn;e kynge &middot; "and I cacche my&yogh;te</L>
<L>Fals or fauel &middot; or any of his feres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>or</I>] other R (<I>in both places</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L>I wolde be wroke of &thorn;o wrecches &middot; &thorn;at worcheth so ille,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;o</I>] &thorn;e C.</NOTE></L>
<L>And don hem hange by &thorn;e hals &middot; and alle &thorn;at hem meynteneth!</L>
<L N="196">Shal neure man of molde &middot; meynprise &thorn;e leste,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of</I>] of &thorn;is W; on O. <I>leste</I>] leeste WO.</NOTE></L>
<L>But ri&yogh;te as &thorn;e lawe wil loke &middot; late falle on hem alle."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wil</I>] wol WC; wole O.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; And comanded a constable &middot; &thorn;at come atte furst,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>come</I>] com W. <I>atte</I>] atte &thorn;e R; at C.</NOTE></L>
<L>To "attache &thorn;o tyrauntz &middot; for eny thynge, I hote,</L>
<L N="200">And fettereth fast falsenesse &middot; for enykynnes &yogh;iftes,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="26"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>enykynnes</I>] any kynnes WC; any kyns O.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000312.tif" N="30, B-text"></L>
<L>And gurdeth of gyles hed &middot; and lat hym go no furthere.</L>
<L>And &yogh;if &yogh;e lacche lyer &middot; late hym nou&yogh;t ascapen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;e</I>] thou C. <I>lacche</I>] laccheth R.</NOTE></L>
<L>Er he be put on &thorn;e pilorye &middot; for eny preyere, I hote;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] C <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="204">And bryngeth Mede to me &middot; maugre hem alle."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bryngeth</I>] brynght C. <I>maugre</I>] maugree W; maugrey O.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Drede atte dore stode &middot; and &thorn;e dome herde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>atte</I>] at &thorn;e WCO.</NOTE></L>
<L>And how &thorn;e kynge comaunded &middot; constables and seriantz,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>comaunded</I>] demede R. ser|iantz] sergeauntz W; sergeantz C; sergeauntis O.</NOTE></L>
<L>Falsenesse and his felawschip &middot; to fettren an to bynden.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>an</I>] and WCRO.</NOTE></L>
<L N="208">&THORN;anne drede went wi&yogh;tliche &middot; and warned &thorn;e fals,</L>
<L>And bad hym flee for fere &middot; and his felawes alle.</L>
