<L>And al &thorn;is maketh me &middot; on &thorn;is meteles to &thorn;ynke;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is meteles</I>] &thorn;eise meteles O; &thorn;is metels WCRB.</NOTE></L>
<L N="168">&para; And how &thorn;e prest preued &middot; no pardoun to dowel,</L>
<L>And demed &thorn;at dowel &middot; indulgences passed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>demed</I>] nempned R. <I>indul|gences</I>] indulgence RCB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Biennales and triennales &middot; and bisschopes lettres,</L>
<L>And how dowel at &thorn;e day of dome &middot; is dignelich vnder|fongen,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="101"></L>
<L>And passeth al &thorn;e pardoun &middot; of seynt petres cherche.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>passeth</I>] passid B. <I>al &thorn;e</I>] alle R. <I>petres</I>] Peter C; Petir B.</NOTE></L>
<L N="173">&para; Now hath &thorn;e pope powere &middot; pardoun to graunte &thorn;e peple</L>
<L>With-outen eny penaunce &middot; to passen in-to heuene;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eny</I>] C <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;is is owre bileue &middot; as lettered men vs techeth,<Q><I>Quodcumque ligaueris super terram, erit ligatum et in celis, &amp;c</I>.</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>] R <I>om. &amp;c</I>.] R <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="176">And so I leue lelly &middot; (lordes forbode ellis!)<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lordes</I>] oure lordis B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at pardoun and penaunce &middot; and preyeres don saue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>saue</I>] &thorn;e same CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Soules &thorn;at haue synned &middot; seuene sithes dedly.</L>
<L>Ac to trust to &thorn;ise triennales &middot; trewly me &thorn;inketh,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ac</I>] And C. <I>trust</I>] trist RB.</NOTE></L>
<L N="180">Is nou&yogh;t so syker for &thorn;e soule &middot; certis, as is dowel.<NOTE PLACE="foot">173&mdash;180. O <I>omits; but in the margin is the note</I>&mdash;now ha&thorn; &thorn;e p.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Is</I>] It is R. <I>soule</I>] saules C; soulis B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; For-&thorn;i I rede &yogh;ow, renkes &middot; &thorn;at riche ben on &thorn;is erthe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>renkes</I>] thenke R; to &thorn;ynk B.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vppon trust of &yogh;owre tresoure &middot; triennales to haue,</L>
<L>Be &yogh;e neuere &thorn;e balder &middot; to breke &thorn;e [ten] hestes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>balder</I>] bolder WCRB. [<I>ten</I> CROB] x LW.</NOTE></L>
<L N="184">And namelich, &yogh;e maistres &middot; mayres and iugges,
<PB REF="00000403.tif" N="121, B-text"></L>
<L>&THORN;at han &thorn;e welthe of &thorn;is worlde &middot; and for wyse men ben holden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for</I>] COBR <I>om</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>To purchace &yogh;ow pardoun &middot; and &thorn;e popis bulles.<MILESTONE N="33" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I>] at O.</NOTE></L>
<L>At &thorn;e dredeful dome &middot; whan ded[e] shullen rise,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dede</I>] <I>so in</I> WCR; &thorn;e dede B; ded L. <I>rise</I>] arise CB.</NOTE></L>
<L N="188">And comen alle bifor cryst &middot; acountis to &yogh;elde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bifor</I>] to-fore W. <I>acountis</I>] and acountes R.</NOTE></L>
<L>How &thorn;ow laddest &thorn;i lyf here &middot; and his lawes keptest,</L>
<L>And how &thorn;ow dedest day bi day &middot; &thorn;e dome wil reherce;<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="102"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dedest</I>] dost R.</NOTE></L>
<L>A poke ful of pardoun &thorn;ere &middot; ne prouinciales lettres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>poke</I>] pook C; pouh&yogh; R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="192">Theigh &yogh;e be founde in &thorn;e fraternete &middot; of alle &thorn;e foure ordres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>foure</I>] fyue R.</NOTE></L>
<L>And haue indulgences double-folde &middot; but if dowel &yogh;ow help,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>indulgences</I>] indulgence CB. <I>if dowel</I>] dowel wil R.</NOTE></L>
<L>I sette &yogh;owre patentes and &yogh;owre pardounz &middot; at one pies hele!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pardounz</I>] pardon WCROB. <I>one</I>] on RB; a O. <I>pies hele</I>] pese hule C; peese hole B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; For-&thorn;i I conseille alle cristene &middot; to crye god mercy,</L>
<L N="196">And Marie his moder &middot; be owre mene bitwene,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>be</I>] &thorn;at she be B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at god gyue vs grace here &middot; ar we gone hennes,</L>
<L>Suche werkes to werche &middot; while we ben here,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>while</I>] &thorn;e while R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at after owre deth-day &middot; dowel reherce,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>deth-day</I>] dede-day C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="200">At &thorn;e day of dome &middot; we dede as he hi&yogh;te.</L>
<TRAILER>[<I>Explicit visio</I> willelmi <I>de</I> petro <I>plowman. Et</I> sequitur <I>vita de dowell, Dobett, et Do-beste</I>, secundum <I>wytt &amp; reson</I>.]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> MS. Camb. Univ. Lib. Ll. 4. 14, <I>in a later hand;</I> cf. Text A.</NOTE></TRAILER>
</LG>

