<HEAD>PASSUS XI. (DO-WEL III.)<NOTE PLACE="foot">TITLE. Passus vndecimus &amp; (<I>sic</I>) supra C; Passus vndecimus W; Passus xus de vis. vt supra R; B <I>adds</I> &amp; quartus de Dowel.</NOTE></HEAD>
<HEAD><I>Passus xj</I><SUP>us</SUP>.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>THanne scripture scorned me &middot; and a skile tolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>scorned</I>] serued C.</NOTE></L>
<L>And lakked me in latyne &middot; and li&yogh;te by me she sette, And seyde, <Q>"<I>multi multa sciunt, &amp; seipsos nesciunt.</I>"</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>] a R. <I>she</I>] he R; COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;o wepte I for wo &middot; and wratth of her speche,<MILESTONE N="44" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wratth</I>] wra&thorn;&thorn;e O; sorwe R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">And in a wynkyng wratth &middot; wex I aslepe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wynkyng</I>] wyndynge COB. <I>wratth</I>] wrath R; wra&thorn;e W; wra&thorn;&thorn;e O; wratthe CB; wrath <I>in</I> Crowley. <I>wex I</I>] <I>so in</I> LCOB; weex I W; til I was R.</NOTE></L>
<L>A merueillouse meteles &middot; mette me &thorn;anne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A</I>] A ful B. <I>meteles</I>] sweuene COB. <I>me</I>] I me O. <I>mette&mdash;&thorn;anne</I>] me tydde to dreme R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I was rauisshed ri&yogh;t &thorn;ere &middot; and fortune me fette,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] For R. <I>and</I>] for R.</NOTE></L>
<L>And in-to &thorn;e londe of longynge &middot; allone she me brou&yogh;te,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] B <I>om. in-to</I>] to C. <I>all|one</I>] &amp; loue R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">And in a myroure &thorn;at hi&yogh;t mydlerd &middot; she mad me to bi|holde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] O <I>om. mydlerd</I>] <I>so in</I> LCB; mydleerd O; myddelerd R; middeler&thorn;e W. <I>to</I>] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Sitthen she sayde to me &middot; "here my&yogh;tow se wondres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sitthen</I>] Sone W. <I>to</I>] vnto O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And knowe &thorn;at &thorn;ow coueytest &middot; and come &thorn;er-to, par aunter."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>par aunter</I>] par aunter R; par|aduenture B.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000451.tif" N="169, B-text"></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;anne hadde fortune folwyng hir &middot; two faire damoy|seles,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>damoyseles</I>] damesels C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12"><I>Concupiscencia-carnis</I> &middot; men called &thorn;e elder mayde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mayde</I>] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And coueytise-of-eyes &middot; ycalled was &thorn;at o&thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ycalled</I>] called CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Pryde-of-parfyte-lyuynge &middot; pursued hem bothe,</L>
<L>And badde me, for my contenaunce &middot; acounte clergye li&yogh;te.</L>
<L N="16">&para; <I>Concupiscencia-carnis</I> &middot; colled me aboute &thorn;e nekke,</L>
<L>And seyde, "&thorn;ow art &yogh;onge and &yogh;epe &middot; and hast &yogh;eres ynowe,</L>
<L>Forto lyue longe &middot; and ladyes to louye;</L>
<L>And in &thorn;is myroure &thorn;ow my&yogh;te se &middot; myrthes ful manye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>] R <I>om. myrthes</I>] my&yogh;tes W.</NOTE></L>
<L N="20">&THORN;at leden &thorn;e wil to lykynge &middot; al &thorn;i lyf tyme."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wil</I>] wole W; wyl C; wel R; wollen B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e secounde seide &thorn;e same &middot; "I shal suwe &thorn;i wille;</L>
<L>Til &thorn;ow be a lorde and haue londe &middot; leten &thorn;e I nelle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I ne shal folwe &thorn;i felawship &middot; if fortune it lyke."</L>
<L>"He shal fynde me his frende" &middot; quod fortune &thorn;er-after;</L>
<L>"&THORN;e freke &thorn;at folwed my wille &middot; failled neuere blisse."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>folwed</I>] folwe&thorn; CR; folwi&thorn; B.</NOTE></L>
