<L>And pryde-of-parfyt-lyuynge &middot; to moche peril &thorn;e brynge."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of</I>] of &thorn;i R. <I>brynge</I>] brou&yogh;t CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "&YOGH;ee, recche &thorn;e neuere," quod recchelesnes &middot; stode forth in ragged clothes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>stode</I>] stonde B.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Folwe forth &thorn;at fortune wole &middot; &thorn;ow hast wel fer til elde;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fer</I>] fare C. <I>til</I>] to RCB.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000452.tif" N="170, B-text"></L>
