<L N="52">And seyde, "haue no conscience &middot; how &thorn;ow come to gode;</L>
<L>Go confesse [&thorn;e] to sum frere &middot; and shewe hym &thorn;i synnes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>&thorn;e</I> RCB] &thorn;ee WO; L <I>om., but the line is marked.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>For whiles fortune is &thorn;i frende &middot; Freres wil &thorn;e louye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Freres</I>] sum frere R. <I>wil</I>] wol WC; wolen OB.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000453.tif" N="171, B-text"></L>
<L>And fecche &thorn;e to her fraternite &middot; and for &thorn;e biseke,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fecche</I>] fette R. <I>biseke</I>] by|seche R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="56">To her priour prouyncial &middot; a pardoun forto haue,</L>
<L>And preyen for &thorn;e, pol bi pol &middot; &yogh;if &thorn;ow be <I>pecuniosus.</I>"<Q><I>Set pena pecuniaria non sufficit pro spiritualibus delictis.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pecuniosus</I> WC] peccuniosus L; pecunious R; peccunyous B. <I>Set</I>] R <I>om. pecuniaria</I> WCOB] <I>written</I> pe|cuniarea <I>in</I> L; pecularia R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; By wissynge of &thorn;is wenche I wrou&yogh;te &middot; here wordes were so swete,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wrou&yogh;te</I>] dede R.</NOTE></L>
<L>Tyl I for&yogh;at &yogh;outhe &middot; and &yogh;arn in-to elde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;arn</I>] yarne C; &yogh;erne O; ran R.</NOTE></L>
