<L N="80">For a baptized man may &middot; as maistres telleth,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>as</I>] as &thorn;ise W; as wel as B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;orugh contricioun come &middot; to &thorn;e heigh heuene;<Q><I>Sola contricio</I> [<I>delet peccatum.</I>]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to</I>] til R. [<I>delet peccatum</I> COB] LWR <I>merely have</I> &amp;c.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Ac a barne with-oute bapteme &middot; may nou&yogh;t so be saued;<MILESTONE N="45" UNIT="folio"><Q><I>Nisi quis renatus fuerit</I> [<I>ex aqua, &amp;c.</I>;]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] W <I>om. so</I>] CB <I>om. saued</I>] ysaued R. [<I>ex aqua, &amp;c</I> COB] LWR <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
