<L>"&YOGH;if I durste," quod I, "amonges men &middot; &thorn;is meteles auowe!"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is meteles</I>] &thorn;eise metelis O.</NOTE></L>
<L>"&YOGH;e, bi peter and bi poule," quod he &middot; "and take hem bothe to witnesse,<Q><I>Non oderis fratres secrete in corde tuo, set publice argue illos.</I>"</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;e</I>] &yogh;he O; &yogh;is W; CB <I>om. take</I>] <I>so in</I> LR; took WC; toke OB. <I>hem</I>] COB <I>om. publice</I>] puplice O.</NOTE></L>
<L N="88">&para; "&THORN;ei wol alleggen also," quod I &middot; "and by &thorn;e gospel preuen,<Q><I>Nolite iudicare quemquam.</I>"</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>quemquam</I>] R <I>adds</I> &amp;c.</NOTE></L>
