<L>Males drowen hem to males &middot; a mornynges bi hem-self,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] on O. <I>mornynges</I>] mor|wenynges WROB; morwenges C.</NOTE></L>
<L>And in euenynges also &middot; &yogh;e[de] males fro femeles.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] O <I>om. &yogh;ede</I>] <I>so in</I> R; <I>miswritten</I> &yogh;e <I>in</I> L, <I>but the line is marked for correction; in other</I> MSS. <I>we find</I>&mdash;&thorn;e males ben fro femelles W; the males fro femeles C; &thorn;e males fro &thorn;e femeles OB.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ere ne was cow ne cowkynde &middot; &thorn;at conceyued hadde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ere</I>] &thorn;e R. <I>ne</I> (1)] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="333">&THORN;at wolde belwe after boles &middot; ne bore after sowe;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>belwe</I>] belwen R.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bothe horse and houndes &middot; and alle other bestes</L>
<L>Medled nou&yogh;te wyth here makes &middot; &thorn;at with fole were.</L>
<L N="336">&para; Briddes I bihelde &middot; &thorn;at in buskes made nestes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>buskes</I>] busches R.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hadde neuere wye witte &middot; to worche &thorn;e leest.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>neuere</I>] nere R. <I>wye</I>] weye R; wi&yogh;th B.</NOTE></L>
<L>I hadde wonder at whom &middot; and where &thorn;e pye lerned</L>
<L>To legge &thorn;e stykkes &middot; in whiche she [leye&thorn;] and bredeth;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>legge</I>] laye C. <I>&thorn;e</I>] R <I>om. she</I>] he COB; a R. [<I>leye&thorn;</I> W] layes C; <I>in</I> L <I>badly spelt</I> leythe; leuth R; ley&yogh;e&thorn; B.</NOTE></L>
<L N="340">&THORN;ere nys wri&yogh;te as I wene &middot; shulde worche hir neste to paye;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nys wri&yogh;te</I>] is no wit R. <I>neste</I>] nestes W.</NOTE></L>
<L>If any masoun made a molde &thorn;er-to &middot; moche wonder it were.</L>
<L>&para; And &yogh;et me merueilled more &middot; how many other briddes<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] Ac W. <I>how</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
