<L N="361">&THORN;at resoun rewarded &middot; and reuled alle bestes,</L>
<L>Saue man and his make; &middot; many tyme and ofte<NOTE PLACE="foot">CB <I>omit. tyme</I>] tymes R.</NOTE></L>
<L>No resoun hem folwed &middot; and &thorn;anne I rebuked<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>No</I>] Ne CB.</NOTE></L>
<L N="364">Resoun, and ri&yogh;te &middot; til hym-seluen I seyde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I</I>] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>"I haue wonder of &thorn;e," quod I &middot; "&thorn;at witty art holden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>holden</I>] holde R.</NOTE></L>
<L>Why &thorn;ow ne suwest man and his make &middot; &thorn;at no mysfait hem folwe?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>suwest</I>] schewest R. <I>mysfait</I>] mysfeet W; mysfaut C; misfeith R; mysfai&thorn; B.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000470.tif" N="188, B-text"></L>
<L>&para; And resoun arated me &middot; and seyde, "recche &thorn;e neuere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] And &thorn;o B.</NOTE></L>
<L N="368">Whi I suffre or nou&yogh;t suffre &middot; &thorn;i-self hast nou&yogh;t to done;</L>
<L>Amende &thorn;ow it, if &thorn;ow my&yogh;te &middot; for my tyme is to abyde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>it</I>] COB <I>om. is</I>] is nou&yogh;t CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Suffraunce is a souereygne vertue &middot; and a swyfte veni|aunce.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I> (1)] COB <I>om. a</I> (2)] of O.</NOTE></L>
<L>Who suffreth more &thorn;an god?" quod he &middot; "no gome, as I leue!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>suffreth</I>] suffres C; suffrede WO. <I>gome</I>] man (<I>with</I> i. gome <I>writ|ten above</I>) C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="372">He mi&yogh;te amende in a Minute while &middot; al &thorn;at mys standeth,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Minute</I>] litel (<I>corrected to</I> mynute) C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac he suffreth for somme mannes good &middot; and so is owre bettre.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>suffreth</I>] suffres C; suffrede O. <I>is</I>] it is W.</NOTE></L>
<L>[&para; Holy writt," quod &thorn;at weye &middot; "wisseth men to suffre;<Q><I>Propter deum subiecti estote omni creature.</I></Q></L>
