<L N="428">Why &yogh;e wisse me &thorn;us," quod I &middot; "was for I rebuked resoun."</L>
<L>&para; "Certes," quod he, "&thorn;at is soth" &middot; and shope hym for to walken;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he</I>] I R. <I>shope</I>] schope R; shoop W. <I>walken</I>] waken R.</NOTE></L>
<L>And I aros vp ri&yogh;t with &thorn;at &middot; and folwed hym after,</L>
<L>And preyed hym of his curteisye &middot; to telle me his name.
</L>
</LG>

