<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000492.tif" N="210, B-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS XIII (DO-WEL V).</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot">TITLE. Passus terciodecimus LCO; Passus xiijus, &amp;c. W; Passus duode|cimus (!) de visione, vt supra R; Passus tercius decimus et Sextus [<I>read</I> Quintus] de dowel B.</NOTE><I>Passus terciodecimus.</I></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>And I awaked &thorn;ere-with &middot; witles nerehande,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>awaked</I>] wakede O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And as a freke &thorn;at fre were &middot; forth gan I walke<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] C <I>om. fre</I>] fere R; fey B. <I>walke</I>] walken R.</NOTE></L>
<L>In manere of a mendynaunt &middot; many a &yogh;ere after,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a mendynaunt</I>] amendement (!) B. <I>a</I> (2)] RCOB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="4">And of &thorn;is metyng many tyme &middot; moche &thorn;ou&yogh;t I hadde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>tyme</I>] tymes R.</NOTE></L>
<L>First, how fortune me failled &middot; at my moste nede,</L>
<L>And how &thorn;at elde manaced me &middot; my&yogh;t we euere meten;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>manaced</I>] mansed R. <I>my&yogh;t&mdash;euere</I>] we mi&yogh;te neuere COB.</NOTE></L>
<L>And how &thorn;at freris folwed &middot; folke &thorn;at was riche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>was</I>] weren O.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">And folke &thorn;at was pore &middot; at litel prys &thorn;ei sette,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>was</I>] weren O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And no corps in her kirke&yogh;erde &middot; ne in her kyrke was buryed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ne</I>] nor W. <I>her</I> (2)] hir (<I>printed</I> his) W; C <I>om. was</I>] were R.</NOTE></L>
<L>But quikke he biquethe hem au&yogh;te &middot; or shulde helpe quyte her dettes.<MILESTONE N="53" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>quikke</I>] &thorn;ei quyk B. <I>he</I>] CB <I>om. hem</I>] hym B; W <I>om. or&mdash;quyte</I>] to quyte wi&thorn; W.</NOTE></L>
<L>And how &thorn;is coueitise ouercome &middot; clerkes and prestes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is</I>] COB <I>om.</I>; &thorn;us R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">And how &thorn;at lewed men ben ladde &middot; but owre lorde hem helpe,</L>
<L>&THORN;orugh vnkonnynge curatoures &middot; to incurable peynes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>peynes</I>] peyne C.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000493.tif" N="211, B-text"></L>
<L>&para; And how &thorn;at ymagynatyf &middot; in dremeles me tolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dremeles</I>] dremes C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of kynde and of his connynge &middot; and how curteise he is to bestes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>his</I>] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="16">And how louynge he is to bestes &middot; on londe and on water;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>] his C. <I>bestes</I>] briddes W.</NOTE></L>
<L>Leueth he no lyf &middot; lasse ne more;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Leueth</I>] Leue&thorn; <I>or</I> Lene&thorn; (<I>printed</I> Leneth) W.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e creatures &thorn;at crepen &middot; of kynde ben engendred.</L>
<L>And sitthen how ymagynatif seyde &middot; <I>vix iustus sal|uabitur</I>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sitthen</I>] COB <I>om. iustus</I>] W <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="20">And whan he had seyde so &middot; how sodeynelich he passed.<NOTE PLACE="foot">14&mdash;20. R <I>omits.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&para; I lay down longe in &thorn;is &thorn;ou&yogh;te &middot; and atte laste I slepte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>down</I>] CB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And, as cryste wolde, &thorn;ere come conscience &middot; to conforte me &thorn;at tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] in &thorn;at R.</NOTE></L>
<L>And bad me come to his courte &middot; with clergye sholde I dyne.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>me</I>] O <I>om. sholde</I>] shul C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">&para; And for conscience of clergye spake &middot; I come wel &thorn;e rather,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>come</I>] com WC; cam RB.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;ere I say a maistre &middot; what man he was I neste,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>say</I>] sei&yogh; WCO. <I>neste</I>] <I>so in</I> LRC; nyste WOB.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at lowe louted &middot; and loueliche to scripture.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>louted</I>] a-loutid B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Conscience knewe hym wel &middot; and welcomed hym faire;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Conscience</I>] Conscien C. <I>wel</I>] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="28">&THORN;ei wesshen and wypeden &middot; and wenten to &thorn;e dyner.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wesshen</I>] wasscheden O; wes|shenden (<I>sic</I>) C. <I>wypeden</I>] wipten B. <I>wenten</I>] wente R; went C. <I>&thorn;e</I>] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
