<L>And, as &thorn;ou demest, wil &thorn;ei do &middot; alle here dayes after;<Q><I>Pacientes vincunt, &amp;c.</I>"]</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot">164&mdash;171. <I>In</I> R <I>only; but cf.</I> C|Text, <I>which has a passage epitomized from it.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "It is but a dido," quod &thorn;is doctour &middot; "a dysoures tale.</L>
