<L>And if [I] rope, ouer-reche &middot; or &yogh;af hem red &thorn;at ropen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nymen&mdash;reche</I>] R <I>om. nymen</I>] and nymen W. [<I>I</I> WCOB] L <I>om. rope</I>] <I>so in</I> C; repe WO; ripye B. <I>ouer-reche</I>] y ouerreche B. <I>or</I>] or (<I>printed</I> of) W; &amp; O. <I>red</I>] reed WO; rede R. <I>ropen</I>] repen RB. <I>Line</I> 374 <I>is marked for correction in</I> L.</NOTE></L>
<L>To seise to me with her sykel &middot; &thorn;at I ne sewe neure.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>To</I>] And COB. <I>seise</I>] seysed B. <I>her</I>] my COB. <I>ne</I>] OB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
