<L>&THORN;at my mynde ne was more &middot; on my gode, in a doute,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] in R. <I>a</I>] O <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;an in &thorn;e grace of god &middot; and his grete helpes:<Q><I>Vbi thesaurus tuus, ibi &amp; cor tuum.</I>"</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Vbi</I>] Vbi est R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="400">[&YOGH;et [&thorn;e] glotoun with grete othes &middot; his [garnement] hadde soyled,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>&thorn;e</I>] <I>must be inserted;</I> R <I>om.</I> [<I>garnement</I>] <I>miswritten</I> granement; <I>but</I> garnement ( = garment) <I>is right.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And foule be-flobered it &middot; as with fals speche;</L>
<L>&THORN;ere no nede ne was &middot; [tok] godes name an Idel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ere</I>] <I>miswritten</I> As &thorn;ere, <I>which is nonsense; it is repeated from</I> Pass. V. l. 377, <I>which see.</I> [<I>tok</I>] <I>must be inserted;</I> R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
