<L>And han likynge to lythen hem &middot; to do &yogh;ow to lawghe;<Q><I>Ve vobis qui ridetis, &amp;c.:</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>han</I>] hase C. <I>lythen</I>] heren B; listem (<I>sic</I>) C. <I>to</I> (3)] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And &yogh;iueth hem mete and Mede &middot; and pore men refuse,</L>
<L>In &yogh;owre deth-deyinge &middot; I drede me ful sore,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ful</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE>
<PB REF="00000515.tif" N="233, B-text"></L>
<L>Lest &thorn;o thre maner men &middot; to moche sorwe &yogh;ow brynge:<Q><I>Consencientes &amp; agentes pari pena punientur.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;o</I>] &thorn;e CO. <I>to moche</I>] to muche to mykil (<I>sic</I>) C. <I>&yogh;ow</I>] R <I>om. punientur</I>] puniendi sunt R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="428">Patriarkes &amp; prophetes &middot; and prechoures of goddes wordes</L>
<L>Sauen &thorn;orw her sarmoun &middot; mannes soule fram helle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sarmoun</I>] sermons W; ser|moun CO; sermon B. <I>mannes soule</I>] manne saule C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ri&yogh;t so flater[er]es and foles &middot; aren &thorn;e fendes disciples,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>flatereres</I>] <I>miswritten</I> flateres <I>in</I> L; <I>but the line is marked for cor|rection. aren</I>] and CO.</NOTE></L>
<L>To entice men &thorn;orw her tales &middot; to synne and harlotrye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>entice</I>] eten (!) C. <I>and</I>] and to WB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac clerkes &thorn;at knowen holywryt &middot; shulde kenne lordes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ac</I>] And C.</NOTE></L>
<L>What dauid seith of suche men &middot; as &thorn;e sauter telleth:<Q><I>Non habitabit in medio domus mee, qui facit superbiam &amp; qui loquitur iniqua:</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>suche</I>] swiche WO; swilc C. <I>&amp;</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Shulde none harlote haue audience &middot; in halle ne in chambres,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>harlote</I>] harlotes CB. <I>ne</I>] nor WR. <I>chambres</I>] chambre WB.</NOTE></L>
