<L N="453">&THORN;ise solaseth &thorn;e soule &middot; til hym-selue be-falle</L>
<L>In a wel [gode] hope, [for he wrou&yogh;te so] &middot; amonges worthi seyntes.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">437&mdash;454. <I>In</I> R <I>only; but found in</I> C-Text. <I>The passage is fairly cor|rect.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>gode</I>] R <I>om.</I> [<I>for he wrou&yogh;te so</I>] R <I>om.</I> But cf. C-Text.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Ac flat[<I>er</I>]eres and foles &middot; &thorn;orw her foule wordes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ac</I>] And C; &THORN;ere R. <I>flat|ereres</I>] <I>miswritten</I> flateres <I>in</I> LR.</NOTE></L>
