<HEAD>PASSUS XIV (DO-WEL VI).</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot">TITLE. Passus quarto-decimus de visione, vt supra CR (<I>but</I> R <I>has</I> xiijus); Passus xiiijus, &amp;c WO; B <I>adds</I> et vijus [<I>read</I> vjus] de dowel.</NOTE><I>Passus xiiij</I><SUP>us</SUP>.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"<B>I</B> Haue but one [hool] hatere," quod haukyn &middot; "I am &thorn;e lasse to blame<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>one</I>] oon WC; on RB; an O. [<I>hool</I> WCOB] LR <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;ough it be soiled and selde clene &middot; I slepe &thorn;ere-inne on ni&yogh;tes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>soiled</I>] soulid B; suyled C. <I>selde clene</I>] foule COB. <I>on</I>] o W.</NOTE></L>
<L>And also I haue an houswyf &middot; hewen and children&mdash;<Q><I>Vxorem duxy, &amp; ideo non possum venire</I>&mdash;</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>an houswyf</I>] a wif CB; a wijf O. <I>hewen</I>] and hewen B. <I>venire</I>] &amp;c. R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at wolen bymolen it many tyme &middot; maugre my chekes!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wolen</I>] walden C; wolden O. <I>bymolen</I>] bifoule C; defoule B. <I>tyme</I>] tymes R. <I>maugre</I>] maugree W; magre B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; It hath ben laued in lente &middot; and oute of lente bothe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lente</I>] lenten R; leaute B (<I>twice</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L N="6">With &thorn;e sope of sykenesse &middot; &thorn;at seketh wonder depe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seketh</I>] sekest CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>And with &thorn;e losse of catel &middot; loth forto agulte<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>loth</I>] bathe C; bo&thorn;e B.</NOTE></L>
<L>God or any gode man &middot; bi au&yogh;te &thorn;at I wiste;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>or</I>] ar R; or (<I>indistinct, and printed</I> of) W.</NOTE></L>
<L>And was shryuen of &thorn;e preste &middot; &thorn;at gaue me, for my synnes,</L>
<L N="10">To penaunce, pacyence &middot; and pore men to fede,</L>
<L>Al for coueitise of my crystenedome &middot; in clennesse to kepen it.
<PB REF="00000518.tif" N="236, B-text"></L>
<L N="12">&para; And couthe I neuere, by cryste &middot; kepen it clene an houre,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>couthe</I>] coude R. <I>neuere</I>] nou&yogh;t R. <I>kepen it</I>] <I>precedes</I> bi crist <I>in</I> B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I ne soiled it with sy&yogh;te &middot; or sum ydel speche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>soiled</I>] soulid B; fouled C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Or &thorn;orugh werke or &thorn;orugh worde &middot; or wille of myn herte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;orugh</I> (2)] CROB <I>om. worde</I>] thou&yogh;t R. <I>or</I> (3)] and other R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at I ne flober it foule &middot; fro morwe tyl eue."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>] But CO. <I>flober</I>] floboure C.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">&para; "And I shal kenne &thorn;e," quod conscience &middot; "of con|tricioun to make,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>kenne</I>] telle B.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at shal clawe &thorn;i cote &middot; of alkynnes filthe,<Q><I>Cordis contricio, &amp;c.:</I>&mdash;</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>clawe &thorn;i cote</I>] &thorn;i cote make clene B. <I>clawe</I>] C <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Dowel [shal] wasshen it and wryngen it &middot; &thorn;orw a wys confessour,<Q><I>Oris confessio, &amp;c.:</I>&mdash;</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>shal</I> W] schal O; LCRB <I>om. it</I> (1)] it (<I>but omitted in printing</I>) W.</NOTE></L>
