<L N="404">But leten hym lede forth what hym lyked &middot; and lete what hym liste.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>what hym</I> (1)] whom hym W; with hym who hym C; with hym alle &thorn;at hym B. <I>what</I> (2)] whom W.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Many hundreth of angeles &middot; harpeden &amp; songen,<Q><I>Culpat caro, purgat caro; regnat deus dei caro.</I></Q></L>
<L>&para; Thanne piped pees &middot; of poysye a note,</L>
<L>"<I>Clarior est solito post maxima nebula phebus</I>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>solito</I>] solitus R. <I>nebula</I>] <I>so in the</I> MSS.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000624.tif" N="342, B-text"></L>
<L N="408"><I>Post inimicitias</I> [<I>clarior est et amor</I>].<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>clarior&mdash;amor</I>] LW <I>omit;</I> RCOBY <I>retain this half-line.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>After sharpe shoures," quod pees &middot; "moste shene is &thorn;e sonne;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sharpe</I>] scharpest R. <I>shene</I>] clene B.</NOTE></L>
