<L>"&YOGH;e, go &thorn;i gate," quod pees &middot; "bi god, for al &thorn;i phisyk,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pees</I>] piers CB. <I>&thorn;i</I> (2)] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="340">But &thorn;ow conne somme crafte &middot; &thorn;ow comest nou&yogh;t her|Inne!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>somme</I>] any R; som oo&thorn;er W. <I>her-Inne</I>] he Inne (<I>sic</I>) R; ther-Inne CB.</NOTE></L>
<L>I knewe such one ones &middot; nou&yogh;te eighte wynter passed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>passed</I>] hennes W.</NOTE></L>
<L>Come in &thorn;us ycoped &middot; at a courte &thorn;ere I dwelt,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Come</I>] And cam B. <I>I</I>] &thorn;at y B. <I>dwelt</I>] dwelde W.</NOTE></L>
<L>And was my lordes leche &middot; &amp; my ladyes bothe.<MILESTONE N="91b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lordes</I>] ladyes CB; lady O. <I>ladyes</I>] lordes C; lordis OB.</NOTE></L>
<L N="344">And at &thorn;e last &thorn;is limitour &middot; &thorn;o my lorde was out,</L>
<L>He salued so owre wommen &middot; til somme were with childe!"</L>
<L>Hende-speche het pees &middot; opene &thorn;e &yogh;ates&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>het</I>] heet WRC; heete O. <I>pees</I>] pees &thorn;o R. <I>opene</I>] to opene O; vppon B.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Late in &thorn;e frere and his felawe &middot; and make hem faire chere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="348">He may se and here &middot; so it may bifalle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>here</I>] here her R. <I>it</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>That lyf &thorn;orw his lore &middot; shal leue coueityse,</L>
<L>And be adradde of deth &middot; and with-drawe hym fram pryde,</L>
<L>And acorde with conscience &middot; and kisse her either other."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>her</I>] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="352">Thus thorw hende-speche &middot; entred &thorn;e frere,</L>
<L>And cam in-to conscience &middot; and curteisly hym grette,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>grette</I>] grete C.</NOTE></L>
<L>"&THORN;ow art welcome," quod conscience &middot; "canstow hele &thorn;e syke?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>canstow</I>] canst &thorn;ou OB. <I>&thorn;e</I>] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Here is contricioun," quod conscience &middot; "my cosyn, ywounded,</L>
<L N="356">Conforte hym," quod conscience &middot; "and take kepe to his sores;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I>] O <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>The plastres of &thorn;e persoun &middot; and poudres biten to sore,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>plastres</I>] plastre B. <I>biten</I>] bitten C; ben R.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000666.tif" N="384, B-text"></L>
<L>He lat hem ligge ouerlonge &middot; and loth is to chaunge hem;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>He</I>] And R. <I>lat</I>] leet C; leete O; lett B. <I>hem</I> (1)] hym C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Fro lenten to lenten &middot; he lat his plastres bite."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lenten</I>] lente R (<I>twice</I>). <I>lat</I>] latte O; lette R; leti&thorn; B. <I>bite</I>] bitte R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="360">&para; "That is ouerlonge," quod this limitour &middot; "I leue I shal amende it;"&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>That</I>] This C.</NOTE></L>
<L>And goth and gropeth contricioun &middot; and gaf hym a plastre<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I> (2)] R <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Of "a pryue payement &middot; and I shal praye for &yogh;ow,</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;at &yogh;e ben holde to &middot; al my lyf tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] And for COB.</NOTE></L>
<L>And make &yogh;ow, my lady &middot; in masse and in matynes,</L>
<L N="365">As freres of owre fraternite &middot; for a litel syluer."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>freres</I>] frere WO.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Thus he goth and gadereth &middot; and gloseth &thorn;ere he shryueth,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>goth</I>] goo&thorn; WO; goos C. <I>gadereth</I>] gadderes C.</NOTE></L>
<L>Tyl contricioun hadde clene for&yogh;eten &middot; to crye &amp; to wepe,</L>
<L N="368">And wake for his wykked werkes &middot; as he was wont to done.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wake</I>] awake C; a-wakid B. <I>was wont</I>] was woned B; woned R.</NOTE></L>
<L>For confort of his confessour &middot; contricioun he lafte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lafte</I>] lefte R.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at is &thorn;e souereynest salue &middot; for alkyn synnes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for</I>] of O. <I>alkyn</I>] alle kynne WROB; alkynne C.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; Sleuth seigh &thorn;at &middot; and so did pryde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seigh</I>] seye R; see C; sei B; &thorn;anne saw O. <I>so</I>] also O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And come with a kene wille &middot; conscience to assaille.</L>
<L N="373">Conscience cryde eft &middot; and bad clergye help hym,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hym</I>] COB <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And also contricioun &middot; forto kepe &thorn;e &yogh;ate.</L>
<L>"He lith and dremeth," seyde pees &middot; "and so do many other;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dremeth</I>] dreint (!) B.</NOTE></L>
<L>The Frere with his phisik &middot; &thorn;is folke hath enchaunted,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hath</I>] hath so R.</NOTE></L>
<L N="377">And plastred hem so esyly &middot; &thorn;ei drede no synne."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>esyly</I>] hesily RB. <I>&thorn;ei</I>] the C.</NOTE></L>
<L>&para; "Bi cryste," quod conscience &thorn;o &middot; "I wil bicome a pilgryme,
<PB REF="00000667.tif" N="385, B-text"></L>
<L>And walken as wyde &middot; as al &thorn;e [worlde] lasteth,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>as</I> (1)] al so B. <I>al</I>] alle R; WO <I>om.</I> [<I>worlde</I> R] world WCOB; wordle L.</NOTE></L>
<L>To seke Piers &thorn;e plowman &middot; &thorn;at pryde may destruye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>seke</I>] seche B. <I>may</I>] my&yogh;te R.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;at freres hadde a fyndyng &middot; &thorn;at for nede flateren,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] B <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="382">And contrepleteth me, conscience; &middot; now kynde me auenge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>contrepleteth</I>] conterpledes C.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sende me happe and hele &middot; til I haue piers &thorn;e plowman!"</L>
<L>And sitthe he gradde after grace &middot; til I gan awake.</L>
<TRAILER><I>Explicit hic dialogus petri plowman.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>So in</I> WCO; Explicit hic B; Passus ijus de Do-best R; O <I>adds</I>&mdash;Lauderis Christe &middot; quia finitur liber iste.</NOTE></TRAILER>
</LG>
