<HEAD>Hic incipit visio Willelmi de Petro Plouhman.</HEAD>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="passus">
<HEAD>[PASSUS I.]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>OBS. P = MS. Phillips (the text); E = MS. Laud 656; I = MS. Il|chester; M = MS. Cotton (Brit. Museum); F = MS. Camb. Ff. 5. 25; G = MS. Camb. Dd. 3. 13; S = MS. Corpus (Camb.); B = Bodley 814, &amp;c. <I>See Preface.</I></P><P>A dagger (&dagger;) in a sidenote marks passages peculiar to the C-text.</P></NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN a somere seyson &middot; whan softe was &thorn;e sonne,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="1"><MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="1"></L>
<L>Y shop [me] in-to shrobbis &middot; as y [a] shepherde were,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>me</I> MFS] PE <I>om. shrobbis</I>] schrubbes FS. [<I>a</I> MFSE] P <I>om. as&mdash;were</I>] a schepard as I were F.</NOTE></L>
<L>In Abit as an Ermite &middot; vnholy of werkes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Abit</I>] an abijt M. <I>as</I>] of M. <I>of</I>] of his F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Ich wente forth in &thorn;e worlde &middot; wonders to hure,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ich wente</I>] Wente i M; Ich wende E. <I>worlde</I>] <I>miswritten</I> worle P.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sawe meny cellis &middot; and selcouthe &thorn;ynges.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] I M. <I>cellis</I>] celles E; selles MF; sellys S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac on a may morwenyng &middot; on Maluerne hulles<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] in MF.</NOTE></L>
<L>Me byfel for to slepe &middot; for weyrynesse of wandryng;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for</I>] M <I>om. wandryng</I>] walk|yng M. F <I>has</I>&mdash;Me be-fel a ferly &middot; a fayr-eye me &thorn;ou&yogh;t (<I>cf.</I> B-text).</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">And in a launde as ich lay &middot; lenede ich and slepte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] M <I>om. lenede ich</I>] i lenede a-doun M.</NOTE></L>
