<L>And honge aboute &thorn;e cattys hals &middot; &thorn;anne hure we mowe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>honge</I>] binde hit M; honge hit S. <I>hals</I>] nekke (<I>with</I> hals <I>above it</I>) S. <I>hure</I>] here M; heere F; hyre G; huyre S. <I>&thorn;anne hure</I>] heere &thorn;anne F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wher he ryt o&thorn;er rest &middot; o&thorn;er romy&thorn; to pleye.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Wher</I>] Where SGE; Whe&thorn;er MF; Wer P. <I>ryt</I>] ritt E; rijt M; ry&yogh;t G; rist F. <I>o&thorn;er</I> (1)] or S. <I>o&thorn;er</I> (2)] or SMF.</NOTE></L>
<L>And yf hym luste for to layke &middot; &thorn;anne loke we mowe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for</I>] M <I>om. layke</I>] walke E. <I>loke</I>] here M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And appere in hus presence &middot; [whyle] hym pleye lyke&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>appere&mdash;presence</I>] in his pre|sence appere F. [<I>whyle</I> SE] whil F; &thorn;e while MG; wil P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="189">And yf he wratthe, we mowe be war &middot; and hus way roume."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>he</I>] hym G. <I>wratthe</I>] wre&thorn;|&thorn;u&thorn; G; wrethe M; wra&thorn; hym E. <I>roume</I>] rowmye E. <I>hus&mdash;roume</I>] of hys wey renne G.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000850.tif" N="12, C-text"></L>
<L>Al &thorn;e route of ratons &middot; to &thorn;ys reison a-sentede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;is MG. <I>ratons</I>] &thorn;e ratons PS; <I>but</I> MFGE <I>omit</I> &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac &thorn;o &thorn;e belle was ybou&yogh;t &middot; and [on] &thorn;e by&yogh;e honged,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;o</I>] M <I>om. ybou&yogh;t</I>] <I>spelt</I> ybou&yogh;th P. [<I>on</I> SMFG] in E; P <I>om. honged</I>] hongede P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="192">Ther was no raton of al &thorn;e route &middot; for al &thorn;e reame of fraunce,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>was</I>] ne was M. <I>of</I>] in SMF. <I>al &thorn;e</I> (1)] &thorn;at M.</NOTE></L>
<L>[&THORN;at durste] haue bounde &thorn;e belle &middot; a-boute &thorn;e cattes necke,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>&thorn;at durste</I> M] &thorn;at durst F; &thorn;at dorste S; &thorn;at derste GE; &thorn;a &thorn;erste P. <I>bounde</I>] honget M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne haue it hongid a-boute hus hals &middot; al engelond to wynne;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ne&mdash;hongid</I>] No hongut hit M; Ne hangid hit F. <I>engelond</I>] engelonnd P.</NOTE></L>
<L>And leten hure labour ylost &middot; and al hure longe trauail.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] &thorn;ei M; And &thorn;anne S; &thorn;o &thorn;ey G. <I>leten</I>] letun hy S; letten al M. <I>al</I>] M <I>om. trauail</I>] studi&yogh;e MG; tyme F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="196">A mous &thorn;at muche good couthe &middot; as me &thorn;o &thorn;ou&yogh;te,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>good</I>] G <I>om. couthe</I>] coude MF. <I>&thorn;ou&yogh;te</I> MFG] <I>spelt</I> &thorn;outhe P; &thorn;o&yogh;t E.</NOTE></L>
<L>Strok for&thorn; sturneliche &middot; and stod by-for hem alle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for&thorn;</I>] for&thorn; &thorn;o M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And to &thorn;e route of ratones &middot; rehercede &thorn;use wordes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;is M.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Thauh we hadde ycullid &thorn;e catte &middot; &yogh;ut sholde &thorn;er come ano&thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ycullid</I>] culde F; culd SG. <I>&thorn;e</I>] a F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="200">To cracchen ous &amp; al oure kynde &middot; &thorn;ouh we crepe vnder benches.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cracchen</I>] <I>so in</I> M; chracchen P; cracche SFG; cracchy E. <I>crepe</I>] crope E.</NOTE></L>
<L>For-&thorn;i ich consaile, for comune profit &middot; lete &thorn;e cat worthe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For-&thorn;i</I> F] For-&thorn;y SG; For|whi M; For &thorn;ei P. <I>worthe</I>] y-wor&thorn;e GM.</NOTE></L>
<L>And neuere be we so bold &middot; &thorn;e belle hym to shewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>neuere&mdash;we</I>] be we neuer F.</NOTE></L>
<L>For ich hurde my syre sayn &middot; seuen &yogh;er passed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>passed</I>] a-passed MG; I-passid F</NOTE></L>
<L N="204">'Ther &thorn;e cat nys bote a kyton &middot; &thorn;e court is ful elynge;'<MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="9"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nys</I>] is SMFG. <I>ful</I>] wel M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Witnesse of holy wryt &middot; who so can rede&mdash;
<PB REF="00000851.tif" N="13, C-text"><Q><I>Ue terre ubi puer est rex: Salamon.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Witnesse</I>] Withnesse&thorn; M: Witnessith F. <I>of</I>] hit M; hit wel F; &thorn;erwith G; at S. <I>rede</I>] hit rede M; wel rede F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich sigge it for me," qua&thorn; &thorn;e mous &middot; "ich seo so muchel after,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sigge</I>] seye SG; sei MF. <I>it</I>] M <I>om. seo</I>] se MFGE.</NOTE></L>
<L>Shal neuere &thorn;e cat ne &thorn;e kyton &middot; by my consail, be greued,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e&mdash;&thorn;e</I>] no cat ne M. <I>&thorn;e</I> (2)] E <I>om. &thorn;e&mdash;kyton</I>] no&thorn;er &thorn;e cat &thorn;e kitoun no&thorn;er F. <I>greued</I>] greuede P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="208">Ne carpen of hure colers &middot; &thorn;at costide me neuere;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>costide</I>] costed E; costned S; costnede F; costunde M; costny&thorn; G.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;auh it costned me catel &middot; by-knowe ich ne wolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>costned</I>] coste F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bote soffren and sigge nouht &middot; and so is &thorn;e beste,</L>
<L>Tyl myschief amende [hem] &middot; &thorn;at meny men chaste&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Tyl</I>] Tyl &thorn;at G. <I>myschief</I>] god M. <I>amende</I> SMFG] amenden PE. [<I>hem</I> SMFGE] hym P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="212">[For] meny mannys malt &middot; we mys wolde distrye,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>For</I> SMFG] And PE. <I>man|nys</I>] mannes E; a mannus F; menes M. <I>mys</I> MFG] myse E; muys S; myes P.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &yogh;e, route of ratons &middot; of rest men a-wake,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;e route</I>] &thorn;e rowtus F. <I>awake</I>] wake S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne were &thorn;e cat of &thorn;e court &middot; And &yogh;onge Kytones to|warde;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ne were</I>] Nere F.</NOTE></L>
<L>For hadde &yogh;e ratones &yogh;oure reed &middot; &yogh;e couthe nat ruelie &yogh;ow-selue."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ratones</I>] rattus al F. <I>ruelie</I>] ruly E; rule SG; rewele M; rewle F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="216">What this metals by-mene&thorn; &middot; &yogh;e men &thorn;at buth murye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>What</I> SMFE] Wat PG. <I>metals</I>] metels M; metelus SF; metaus E. <I>by-mene&thorn;</I>] meny&thorn; G. <I>buth</I>] bu&thorn; S; be&thorn; E; by&thorn; G; ben M; be F; <I>miswritten</I> but P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Diuine &yogh;e, for ich ne dar &middot; by dere god almy&yogh;ty!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Diuine</I>] Deme E.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;ut mette me more &middot; of mene and of ryche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;ut</I>] And &yogh;ut M; &amp; &yogh;it F. <I>mette</I> SMFGE] mete P. <I>me</I>] i MF.</NOTE></L>
<L>As barouns &amp; burgeis &middot; and bonde-men of &thorn;roupes,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="6"><MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="10"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>As</I>] Of M. <I>&amp;&middot; burgeis</I>] of burgeises M. <I>&thorn;roupes</I>] &thorn;ropus SF; &thorn;ropes ME; thorpys G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="220">Al ich sauh slepyng &middot; as &yogh;e shullen hure after;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ich sauh</I>] saw I F. <I>hure</I>] i-here M; here F. <I>&yogh;e&mdash;hure</I>] I schal telle S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e bakers and brywers &middot; bouchers and o&thorn;ere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bo&thorn;e</I>] M <I>om.</I></NOTE>
<PB REF="00000852.tif" N="14, C-text"></L>
<L>Webbesters and walkers &middot; and wynners with handen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Webbesters</I>] As websterus F. <I>and</I>] an P. <I>handen</I>] <I>so in</I> E; honn|dus S; hondes M; handes F; handys G.</NOTE></L>
<L>As taylours and tanners &middot; and tyliers of erthe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>As</I>] M <I>om. tanners</I>] tauer|nerus S. <I>of</I>] &thorn;e (<I>sic</I>) SF.</NOTE></L>
<L N="224">As dikers and deluers &middot; &thorn;at don here dedes ille,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>As</I>] M <I>om. dikers&mdash;deluers</I>] deluers and dykers G. <I>&thorn;at</I>] &thorn;ei M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And dryue&thorn; for&thorn; hure daies &middot; with '<I>deux saue dame emme!</I>'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hure daies</I>] &thorn;e longe day M; &thorn;e deerne day F. <I>saue</I>] vous saue G.</NOTE></L>
<L>Kokes and here knaues &middot; crieden 'hote pyes, hote!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>crieden</I>] crien M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Good goos and grys &middot; go we dyne, gowe!'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>goos&mdash;grys</I>] griis and gees M. <I>go we</I>] with gowe F. <I>dyne</I>] to dyner S.</NOTE></L>
<L N="228">Tauerners 'a tast for nouht' &middot; tolden &thorn;e same,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>tolden</I>] &thorn;ei tolde F. <I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;at M; me &thorn;e G.</NOTE></L>
<L>'Whit wyn of oseye &middot; and of gascoyne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Whit</I>] With M; With white F. <I>of</I> (2)] eke of M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of &thorn;e ruele and of &thorn;e rochel wyn &middot; &thorn;e roste to defye.'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Of</I>] &amp; of F. <I>ruele</I>] ruel E; rule SG; rewle M; ryne F. <I>of</I>] SMF <I>om. &thorn;e rochel</I>] rochel SMF. <I>wyn</I>] MG <I>om. &thorn;e</I> (3)] E <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Al &thorn;is ich sauh slepynge &middot; and seuene sythes more.</L>
