<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="passus"><PB REF="00000853.tif" N="15, C-text">
<HEAD>PASSUS II.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot">TITLE. <I>So in</I> IFES; Hic incipit secundus passus de uisione Willelmi de petro plouhman M.</NOTE><I>Incipit passus secundus.</I></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>WHat &thorn;e montayne by-mene&thorn; &middot; and &thorn;e merke dale,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="7"><MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="11"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>by-mene&thorn;</I>] meenes I.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;e feld ful of folke &middot; ich shal &yogh;ow fayre shewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] al &thorn;e I.</NOTE></L>
<L>A loueliche lady of lere &middot; in lynnen y-clo&thorn;id,</L>
<L N="4">Cam doun fro &thorn;at castel &middot; and calde me by name,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Cam</I>] Com hir I. <I>doun</I>] a-doun M. <I>fro</I>] of G. <I>&thorn;at castel</I>] a castel M; &thorn;e clif FS; &thorn;at hul I. <I>calde</I>] clepede M. <I>by name</I>] my name E; faire MIFS.</NOTE></L>
<L>And seide, "wille, slepest &thorn;ow &middot; syxt &thorn;ow &thorn;is puple,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wille</I>] sone IB. <I>syxt</I>] sixst FS; seest M; seist E. <I>syxt &thorn;ow</I>] seestow I. <I>&thorn;ow</I>] &thorn;ou nat F.</NOTE></L>
<L>How busy &thorn;ai ben &middot; a-boute &thorn;e mase?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>How</I>] &amp; how F. <I>&thorn;ai</I>] &thorn;at &thorn;ei MIF. <I>a-boute</I>] al a-bou&yogh;te M; and al aboute I; ry&yogh;t a-boute G.</NOTE></L>
<L>The most partie of &thorn;e puple &middot; &thorn;at passe&thorn; on &thorn;is erthe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>partie</I>] part F. <I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;is MG. <I>&thorn;is</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="8">Haue thei worship in &thorn;is worlde &middot; &thorn;ei willen no betere;<NOTE PLACE="foot">F <I>transposes these lines.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Haue</I>] <I>so in</I> IFEG; Hadden SM; Haued P. <I>in</I>] on G. <I>worlde</I>] er&thorn;e G. <I>&thorn;ei&mdash;betere</I>] wolde &thorn;ey no betre I; &thorn;ei wesche no more F. <I>wil|len</I>] wilne&thorn; MB.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of o&thorn;er heuene &thorn;an here &middot; &thorn;ei holden no tale."<NOTE PLACE="foot">F <I>transposes these lines.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>here</I>] here is IF. <I>&thorn;ei holden</I>] holden &thorn;ei MIF.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich was aferd of hure face &middot; thauh hue faire were,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hue</I>] sche MIFS; heo G; &yogh;o E.</NOTE></L>
<L N="11">And saide, "mercy, ma dame &middot; what may &thorn;ys be to mene?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>what</I>] wat P.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000854.tif" N="16, C-text"></L>
<L>"The tour vp-on toft," qua&thorn; hue &middot; "treuthe ys &thorn;er-ynne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vp-on</I>] vpon &thorn;e ISG; on &thorn;e MF. <I>hue</I>] sche IFS; heo G; &yogh;o E.</NOTE></L>
<L>And wolde &thorn;at &yogh;e wrouhte &middot; as hus word teche&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot">ll.11-13. <Q><L>And seide, merci, ma|dame &middot; For mari&yogh;e loue of heuene,</L><L>&THORN;e tour on &thorn;e toft &middot; what mai it bi-mene?</L><L>&THORN;at tour, quod &thorn;at ladi &middot; treu&thorn;e is &thorn;er-inne M.</L></Q></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] He M. <I>as&mdash;teche&thorn;</I>] as his wille were M; after hys wordes G.</NOTE></L>
<L>For he is fader of faith &middot; and formour of alle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>faith</I>] fey G.</NOTE></L>
<L>To be faith-ful to hym &middot; he &yogh;aue &yogh;ow fyue wittes<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>faithful</I>] feyful G. <I>to</I>] wyth G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">For to worshepen hym &thorn;er-with &middot; while &yogh;e lyuen here.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] M <I>om. while</I>] <I>so</I> M; whyle S; &thorn;e whiles I; whil &thorn;at F; wile P. <I>lyuen</I>] be F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wherfore he het &thorn;e elementes &middot; to helpe &yogh;ow alle tymes,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="8"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Wherfore</I>] Werfore P; &thorn;erfore E. <I>&thorn;e elementes</I>] <I>so</I> MB; &thorn;elementz I; &thorn;e element FS; &thorn;e elemens PE; &thorn;at element G. <I>to</I>] schold G; M <I>om. alle</I>] at al E.</NOTE></L>
<L>And brynge forth &yogh;oure bylyue &middot; bo&thorn;e lynnen and wollen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bylyue</I>] byleue FEG. <I>lynnen&mdash;wollen</I>] wollen &amp; lynnen SF.</NOTE></L>
<L N="19">And in mesure, &thorn;ouh hit muche were &middot; to make &yogh;ow at ese.<NOTE PLACE="foot">G <I>omits. And</I>] MF <I>om. hit</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>He comaundid of his cortesye &middot; in comune &thorn;re &thorn;ynges,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>He</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Aren non nudful bote &thorn;o &thorn;re &middot; nempnen hem ich &thorn;enke,<MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="12"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Aren</I>] Ben M; Were G. <I>nud|ful&mdash;&thorn;re</I>] so nedful as &thorn;o M. <I>&thorn;re</I>] F <I>om. nempnen</I>] and nemene M; &amp; nemne I; &amp; nempne F; nemme S; nemny G.</NOTE></L>
<L>And rekene hem by rewe &middot; reherce hem wher &thorn;e lyke&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wher</I>] wer P.</NOTE></L>
<L>The ferst of &thorn;o ys fode &middot; and vesture &thorn;e secounde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>The</I>] Ther P. <I>of &thorn;o</I>] of hem M; I <I>om. and</I>] an P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">And drynke &thorn;at do &thorn;e good &middot; ac drynk nat oute of tyme.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>do &thorn;e</I>] doth &thorn;e I; it doo&thorn; F. <I>ac</I>] and IG; but MF. <I>drynk</I>] do hit M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Lo! loth in hus lyue &middot; &thorn;orw lecherouse drynke<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Lo</I>] Loke how M; I <I>om. loth</I>] loot S. <I>drynke</I>] drenke P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wikkydlich wroghte &middot; and wratthede god al-myghty.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wroghte</I>] he wrou&yogh;te M. <I>Wik|kydlich wroghte</I>] Wrou&yogh;t wikkede|liche F.</NOTE></L>
<L>In hus dronkenesse a day &middot; hus douhtres he dighte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dronkenesse</I>] <I>so</I> MI; drunken|esse F; dronknesse PSG; derknesse (!) E. <I>a</I>] on a FB. <I>douhtres</I>] doutren M; dou&yogh;tryn G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">And lay by hem bo&thorn;e &middot; as &thorn;e bok telle&thorn;.</L>
<L>In hus glotenie [he] by-gat &middot; [gerles] &thorn;at weren churles,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>he</I> MFS] PIEG <I>om. by-gat</I>] gat MF. [<I>gerles</I> I] gurles MG; gur|lus FS; PE <I>om. weren</I>] <I>miswritten</I> wereren P. <I>churles</I>] &thorn;rallus F.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000855.tif" N="17, C-text"></L>
<L>And al he wited &thorn;e wyne &middot; hus wikked dede.<Q><I>Inebriamus eum uino et dormiamus cum eo, ut seruare possimus de patre nostro semen . Genesis.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wited</I>] witte hit M; wyted hit S; witte I; wyste (<I>over erasure</I>) G. <I>hus</I>] &thorn;at F; &thorn;ys G. <I>et dormiamus</I>] dormiamusque I. <I>seruare</I>] reseruare FS.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thorgh wyn and &thorn;orw wommen &middot; &thorn;er was loth encom|bred;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wommen</I>] womman MI. <I>loth</I>] lot SE. <I>encombred</I>] y-comeryd G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="32">For-&thorn;y dred dilitable drynke &middot; bo&thorn;e day and ny&yogh;tes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For-&thorn;y</I>] For-whi M; F <I>om. day</I>] <I>so</I> IFEG; daies M; dayuus S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mesure is medecyne &middot; &thorn;auh &thorn;ou muche wylne.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>] is a P; <I>but</I> MIFSEGB <I>omit</I> a. <I>wylne</I>] &yogh;erne I.</NOTE></L>
