<HEAD>PASSUS VI.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="foot">TITLE. <I>So</I> ESFG; Hic incipit passus sextus de uisione M; Passus quintus de visione, vbi prius I.</NOTE><I>Incipit passus sextus.</I></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Thus ich a-waked, god wot &middot; whanne ich wonede on cornehulle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a-waked</I>] haue waked F. <I>god wot</I> MFE] wot god PSI. <I>whanne</I>] wanne P. <I>on</I>] in I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Kytte and ich in a cote &middot; clo&thorn;ed as a lollere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>clo&thorn;ed</I>] y-clo&thorn;ed EI.</NOTE></L>
<L>And lytel [y-lete] by &middot; leyue me for so&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] And a P; <I>but</I> IMSE <I>omit</I> a; &amp; ful F. [<I>y-lete</I> IMSG] late F; <I>miswritten</I> ich let P; ich lete E. <I>leyue</I>] leue ME; leueth IFG; by|leuu&thorn; S.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Among lollares of london &middot; and lewede heremytes;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lollares</I>] lollers EI; lollardus F; loreles M. <I>london</I> S] londen <I>or</I> london P; londen EM; londoun IF. <I>heremytes</I>] hermites I; ermi&yogh;tes M.</NOTE></L>
<L>For ich made of &thorn;o men &middot; as reson me tauhte.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>made</I>] rou&yogh;te F.</NOTE></L>
<L>For as ich cam by conscience &middot; with reson ich mette<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For as</I>] &amp; &thorn;o F. <I>with</I>] wit P; M <I>om. ich</I>] me M.</NOTE></L>
<L>In an hote heruest &middot; whenne ich hadde myn hele,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whenne</I>] wenne P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="8">And lymes to labore with &middot; and louede wel fare,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fare</I>] to fare MFS.</NOTE></L>
<L>And no dede to do &middot; bote drynke and to slepe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to do</I>] for to doo F. <I>drynke</I>] to drynke S. <I>and to</I>] and S; wel and F.</NOTE></L>
<L>In hele and in vnite &middot; on me aposede;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vnite</I>] inwitte I; hete F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Romynge in remembraunce &middot; thus reson me aratede.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Romynge</I>] &amp; romyng F; Rom|blynge (= <I>rambling</I>) M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="12">"Canstow seruen," he seide &middot; "o&thorn;er syngen in a churche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Canstow</I>] Canst &thorn;ow MFS; Can &thorn;ou I. <I>a</I>] E <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;er coke for my cokers &middot; o&thorn;er to &thorn;e cart picche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>coke</I>] coken M; loke (<I>wrongly</I>) I. <I>my</I>] S <I>om. cokers</I>] cokares I; cokerus FS.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000921.tif" N="83, C-text"></L>
<L>Mowe o&thorn;er mowen &middot; o&thorn;er make bond to sheues,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mowen</I>] mouwen M; muwe F; mywen I (<I>mow</I> = to put in a mow, to stack). <I>bond</I>] bend F. <I>to</I>] for M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Repe o&thorn;er be a repereyue &middot; and a-ryse erliche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>repereyue</I>] repereue IF; rip|reue M; rippreue E; rype-reue SG. <I>erliche</I>] vp erli M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="16">O&thorn;er haue an horne and be haywarde &middot; and liggen oute a nyghtes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>haue</I>] with F. <I>and</I>] F <I>om. be</I>] be an ME; be a S. <I>oute</I>] &thorn;er|oute I. <I>a</I>] on M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And kepe my corn in my croft &middot; fro pykers and &thorn;eeues?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] To F. <I>fro</I>] for MF. <I>pykers</I>] prikieres M. <I>and</I>] or M.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;er shappe shon o&thorn;er clo&thorn;es &middot; o&thorn;er shep o&thorn;er kyn kepe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>shon&mdash;clo&thorn;es</I>] clo&thorn;us o&thorn;ur schoon F. <I>clo&thorn;es</I>] clo&thorn;e MI.</NOTE></L>
<L>Heggen o&thorn;er harwen &middot; o&thorn;er swyn o&thorn;er gees dryue,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Heggen</I> IMF] Eggen PES. <I>harwen</I>] harewen MS. <I>swyn</I>] swyne kepe E. <I>gees</I>] hogges M.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;er eny [o&thorn;er] kyns craft &middot; &thorn;at to &thorn;e comune nede&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eny</I>] E <I>om.</I> [<I>o&thorn;er</I> MIFSG] PE <I>om. kyns</I>] kynnes MES; kyn F. <I>&thorn;e</I>] E <I>om. nede&thorn;</I> IME] nude&thorn; P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="21">Hem &thorn;at bedreden be &middot; by-lyue to fynde?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bedreden</I>] be-dradde F; in drede M. <I>by-lyue</I>] by-leue E; lijf|lode M. I <I>has</I>&mdash;&thorn;ey I be betered &thorn;e by &middot; &thorn;at by-leue &thorn;e fynden.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Certes," ich seyde &middot; "and so me god helpe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Certes</I>] Certes nai M; Certus sir F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich am to waik to worche &middot; with sykel o&thorn;er with sythe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>waik</I>] woke E; wow M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">And to long, leyf me &middot; lowe for to stoupe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>leyf</I>] lef &thorn;ow M. <I>for</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>To worchen as a workeman &middot; eny whyle to dure."<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] S <I>om. whyle</I>] wyle P.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Thenne hauest &thorn;ow londes to lyue by" &middot; quath reson, "o&thorn;er lynage riche<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hauest</I>] hast IMFSE. <I>londes</I>] land M. <I>quath reson</I>] quod he F (<I>inserted after</I> &thorn;ow).</NOTE></L>
<L>That fynden &thorn;e &thorn;y fode? &middot; for an ydel man &thorn;ow semest,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fynden</I>] fynde&thorn; MIFS. <I>&thorn;e</I>] &thorn;e &thorn;us F. <I>an</I>] F <I>om. ydel</I>] hydel P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="28">A spendour &thorn;at spende mot &middot; o&thorn;er a spille-tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>spende</I>] spene I.</NOTE></L>
