<L>O&thorn;er faitest vp-on frydays &middot; o&thorn;er feste-dayes in churches,<NOTE PLACE="foot">M <I>omits.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>The whiche is lollarene lyf &middot; &thorn;at lytel ys preysed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whiche</I>] wiche P. <I>lollarene</I>] lollerne I; lollerus F; a lollerus S; loreles M; <I>miswritten</I> sollarene E. <I>&thorn;at&mdash;ys</I>] and litel M. <I>preysed</I>] I|preysed IMFS.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000922.tif" N="84, C-text"></L>
<L N="32">&THORN;er ryghtfulnesse rewarde&thorn; &middot; ryght as men deserue&thorn;,<Q><I>Reddit unicuique iuxta opera sua.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ryghtfulnesse</I>] as ri&yogh;t F. <I>Red|dit</I>] Reddet MF.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;er &thorn;ow art broke, so may be &middot; in body o&thorn;er in membre,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>art</I> IMFS] ert PE. <I>broke</I>] croket M.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;er ymaymed &thorn;orw som mys-hap &middot; wher-by &thorn;ow my&yogh;t be excused?"<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wher-by</I>] wer-by P; where|&thorn;urgh F.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Whanne ich &yogh;ong was," quath ich &middot; "meny &yogh;er hennes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Whanne</I>] Wanne P. <I>quath ich</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="36">My fader and my frendes &middot; founden me to scole,</L>
<L>Tyl ich wiste wyterliche &middot; what holy wryt menede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>what</I>] wat P. <I>menede</I>] bi|menede M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And what is best for &thorn;e body &middot; as &thorn;e bok telle&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>what</I>] wat P. <I>is</I>] was FS.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sykerest for &thorn;e soule &middot; by so ich wolle continue.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] &amp; also F. <I>by so</I>] so &thorn;at MF.</NOTE></L>
<L N="40">And &yogh;ut fond ich neuere in faith &middot; sytthen my frendes deyden,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;ut</I>] IF <I>om. ich</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Lyf &thorn;at me lyked &middot; bote in &thorn;es longe clothes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lyked</I>] liked wel F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Yf ich by laboure sholde lyue &middot; and lyflode deseruen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Yf</I>] &yogh;if MFSE; Hyf P; And &yogh;if I.</NOTE></L>
<L>That labour &thorn;at ich lerned best &middot; &thorn;er-with lyue ich sholde;<Q><I>In eadem uocatione [in] qua uocati estis, [manete.]</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>best</I>] furst M. <I>&thorn;er-with</I>] &thorn;er|whit P. <I>sholde</I>] wolde E. [<I>in</I> M] PEIFS <I>om.</I> [<I>manete</I> M] PEIFS <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="44">And ich lyue in londone &middot; and on londone bothe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] And so I. <I>londone</I> MSE] londoun IF; londene P. <I>on londone</I> SE] on londen P; by londoun F; out of londone M; vp-londe I.</NOTE></L>
<L>The lomes &thorn;at ich laboure with &middot; and lyflode deserue</L>
