<L N="176">And constantyn shal be here cook &middot; and couerer of here churche.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>constantyn</I>] costantyn P. <I>shal</I>] S <I>om. couerer</I>] keuerour FS; ceuerour M. <I>churche</I>] kyrke M; chirches IG; kychene S.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000930.tif" N="92, C-text"></L>
<L>For &thorn;e abbot of engelonde . and &thorn;e abbesse hys nece<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e abbesse</I>] abbace F; abbas M. <I>hys</I>] ys P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Shullen haue a knok on here crounes &middot; and in-curable &thorn;e wounde;<Q><I>Contriuit dominus baculum impiorum, uirgam dominancium, plaga in-sanabili.</I><MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="160"></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>knok</I>] knotte F. <I>on</I>] vpon I. <I>here crounes</I>] &thorn;e croune M. <I>wounde</I> IFSE] wonde P. <I>and&mdash;wounde</I>] in|curable schulle &thorn;ei wende M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac er &thorn;at kyng come &middot; as cronycles me tolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">I <I>omits. er</I>] er &thorn;an M; ar S; or FE. <I>&thorn;at</I>] &thorn;is S.</NOTE></L>
<L N="180">Clerkus and holychurche &middot; shal be clo&thorn;ed newe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>churche</I>] kirke <I>would better suit the metre.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And sitthe he consailed &thorn;e kyng &middot; hus comune to louye;<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="54"><MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="59"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to</I>] S <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;e comune ys &thorn;e kynges tresour &middot; conscience wot wel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] F <I>om. &thorn;e</I>] F <I>om. con|science</I>] as conscience F.</NOTE></L>
<L>And al-so," quath reson &middot; "ich rede &yogh;ow riche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>riche</I>] &thorn;at be riche F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="184">And comuners to a-corden &middot; in alle kynne treuthe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And&mdash;a-corden</I>] Acordeth with &thorn;e comune F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Let no kynne consail &middot; ne couetyse &yogh;ow departe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>kynne</I>] kynges M; careful F. <I>couetyse</I>] conscience M. <I>departe</I>] parte I; to parte M.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at on wit and on wil &middot; alle &yogh;oure wardes kepe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] o IFS (<I>twice</I>).</NOTE></L>
<L>Lo! in heuene an hy &middot; was an holy comune,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>heuene&mdash;hy</I>] in &thorn;e heye heuene F; heuen and in er&thorn;e I.</NOTE></L>
<L N="188">Til lucifer &thorn;e lyere &middot; leyued &thorn;at hym-selue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>leyued</I>] leued IMFSE.</NOTE></L>
<L>Were wittyour and worthiour &middot; &thorn;an he &thorn;at was hus maister.</L>
<L>Hold &yogh;ow in vnite &middot; and [he] &thorn;at o&thorn;er wolde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hold</I>] Holde&thorn; M. <I>Hold&mdash;in</I>] Holliche holduth F. [<I>he</I> IMSEG] &yogh;e P. <I>he &thorn;at</I>] ho so F. <I>o&thorn;er</I>] ho&thorn;er P. <I>wolde</I>] wille F.</NOTE></L>
