<HEAD>CONFESSIO SUPERBIE.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Confessio superbie</I>] <I>so in</I> PEG; Superbia F.</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>"Ich, pruyde, pacientliche &middot; penaunce ich aske;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ich</I>] In F. <I>pruyde</I>] pride IMFE. <I>pacientliche</I>] pacientliche quod heo F. <I>ich</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>For ich formest and ferst &middot; to fader and to moder<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to</I>] to my I (<I>twice</I>). <I>to</I> (2)] F <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="16">Haue ybe vnboxome &middot; ich biseche god of mercy;<NOTE PLACE="foot">S <I>has</I> Haue vnbuxum y-be, <I>omitting all words between.</I></NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ybe</I>] be IF; ben M. <I>of</I>] EG <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And vnboxome ybe &middot; nouht a-baissed to a-gulte<NOTE PLACE="foot">S <I>has</I> Haue vnbuxum y-be, <I>omitting all words between.</I></NOTE>,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] Ful F. <I>ybe</I>] i-be M; haue I be F. <I>a-baissed</I>] abasscht I; abassched M; a-baschid S; a-gaste E. <I>nouht a-baissed</I>] abesched me nat F. <I>a-gulte</I>] agilte I; gilte F.</NOTE></L>
<L>God and alle good men &middot; so gret was myn herte;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>God</I>] To god F. <I>alle</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
