<L>And scorned hem and o&thorn;ere &middot; yf [ich] a skyle founde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>o&thorn;ere</I>] sum o&thorn;ur F. [<I>ich</I> E] i MIFS; y G; P <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Lauhynge al a-loude &middot; for lewede men sholde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Lauhynge</I>] With lawhing F. <I>al</I>] E <I>om. men</I>] F <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="24">Wene &thorn;at ich were witty &middot; and wyser &thorn;an a-no&thorn;ere;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Wene</I>] FM <I>put this at end of</I> l. 23. <I>witty</I>] withtiere M; wittyere S. <I>a-no&thorn;ere</I>] o&thorn;er E.</NOTE></L>
<L>Scorner and vnskilful &middot; to hem &thorn;at skil shewede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Scorner</I>] As scornere F.</NOTE></L>
