<L>O&thorn;er-wise &thorn;an ich haue &middot; with-ynne o&thorn;er with-oute,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>haue</I>] hadde F.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000934.tif" N="96, C-text"></L>
<L>Me [wilnynge] &thorn;at men wende &middot; ich were, [as] in aueyr,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Me wilnynge</I>] <I>such must be the true reading, though miswritten</I> Me wynnynge I; Me wilne&thorn; M; Me wilned PESG; I willede F. <I>It is merely a variation of</I> Hym wilnynge <I>in</I> B-text, xiii. 280 (<I>footnote</I>); <I>cf.</I> l. 41. [<I>as</I> IMFESG] P <I>om. aueyr</I>] auoir F (<I>correctly</I>); <I>corrupted to</I> an eyre E; noon o&thorn;ur SG; maner I; i am nau&yogh;t M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="33">Riche, and resonable &middot; and ryghtful of lyuynge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Riche</I>] Bo&thorn;e riche S; Bo&thorn;e ri&yogh;tful F. <I>ryghtful&mdash;lyuynge</I>] ryche with alle F.</NOTE></L>
