<L N="136">For hue hadde a childe in the chapon-cote &middot; hue worth chalenged at eleccion.'<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>] IMFS <I>om. chapon</I>] capoun EF; capen M. <I>hue&mdash;eleccion</I>] chalangeable heo semeth F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thus &thorn;ei sitte, &thorn;o sustres &middot; som tyme, and disputen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Thus&mdash;sustres</I>] Before &thorn;e eleccioun &thorn;e sustrus sitte F. <I>&thorn;ei&mdash;&thorn;o</I>] sitte &thorn;ey I; sitten to M. <I>sustres</I>] susteren MS. <I>and</I>] &amp; &thorn;us F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Til '&thorn;ow lixt' and '&thorn;ow lixt' &middot; be lady ouer hem alle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lixt</I> EIMFS] luxt P. <I>lady</I>] ledere F. <I>hem alle</I>] bo&thorn;e M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;enne a-wake ich, wratthe &middot; and wold be auenged.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] M <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="140">&THORN;anne ich crie and cracche &middot; with my kene nailes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&THORN;anne</I>] And &thorn;anne IMF. <I>kene</I>] longe M.</NOTE></L>
