<L>To haue remissioun and relees &middot; on &thorn;at rental ich leue.]<MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="98"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>From</I> IG; PEMS <I>om.; cf.</I> B. vi. 91, 92.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I> G] a I. <I>relees</I> G] reles I.</NOTE></L>
<L>The [kirke] shal haue my caroyne &middot; and kepe my bones,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>kirke</I> IM] churche PESG.</NOTE></L>
<L N="101">For of my corn and catel &middot; he crauede my tythe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I>] and of my I; and my M. <I>my tythe</I>] me ti&thorn;e I; me te&thorn;e S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ich payed hit prestliche &middot; for peril of my soule,</L>
<L>He is holdinge, ich hope &middot; to haue me in hus masse,<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="79"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>] his P. <I>holdinge</I>] <I>so</I> PI; holdyng EMS; holden G.</NOTE></L>
<L>And menge me in hus memorie &middot; among alle cristine.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>menge</I>] mynge I.</NOTE></L>
<L N="105">My wyf shal haue of &thorn;at ich wan &middot; with treuthe, and no more,</L>
<L>And dele hit among my douhtres &middot; and my dere children.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hit</I>] M <I>om. dere</I>] leue M. <I>children</I>] childres I.</NOTE></L>
<L>For &thorn;auh ich deyde &thorn;ys day &middot; my dettes ben quyted;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>deyde</I>] deied E; deye ISG; dei&yogh;e M. <I>&thorn;ys</I>] to IG. <I>dettes ben</I>] dette is IG. <I>quyted</I>] y-quyted IS; a-quited G; quite M.</NOTE></L>
