<L N="120">And ouer-seyh hem hym-self &middot; ho so best wrouhte,</L>
<L>He sholde be hyred &thorn;er-after &middot; when heruest-tyme come.<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="80"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>when</I>] wen P.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;enne seten some &middot; and songen atten ale,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>atten ale</I>] atte nale G; atte ale I; at &thorn;e ale M; at &thorn;e nale E; ate ale S.</NOTE></L>
