<L>Ar fewe &yogh;eres be fulfilled &middot; famyne shal aryse,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ar</I>] Or E; Er M; And ar I.</NOTE></L>
<L N="348">And so seith <I>saturnus</I> &middot; and sent &yogh;ow to warne.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] An P. <I>saturnus</I>] satur|nes M; saturne I. <I>&yogh;ow</I>] vs I; ous G. <I>warne</I>] warnyng M.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;orwe flodes and foule wederes &middot; frutes shullen faile,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>and</I>] and &thorn;orgh I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Pruyde and pestilences &middot; shal muche puple fecche.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Pruyde</I>] Prude E; Pride IM. <I>pestilences</I>] pestelences P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="351">Thre shupes and a shaft &middot; with an vm. folwyng,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>shupes</I>] schypes I; schippes M. <I>shaft</I>] schaeff I. <I>an vm</I>] a vin M. <I>vm</I>] <I>so</I> PE; I <I>seems to have</I> .viij. Crowley <I>quotes this line thus</I>&mdash;Three shyppes and a shefe, wyth an eight folowynge; <I>see</I> Pref. B. xxxiv.</NOTE></L>
<L>Shal brynge bane and bataile &middot; on bothe half &thorn;e mone.<NOTE PLACE="foot">ll. 351-352. G <I>omits.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;anne shal de&thorn; with-drawe &middot; and derthe be Iustice,</L>
<L>And dawe &thorn;e deluere &middot; deye for defaute,</L>
<L N="355">Bote god of hus goodnesse &middot; graunte ous a trewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Bote</I>] Bot &yogh;if IG. <I>hus</I>] E <I>om. trewe</I>] truwe E; treu&thorn;e M.</NOTE></L>
<TRAILER><I>Hic explicit passus nonus.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>So</I> PG; <I>so also</I> E, <I>omitting</I> Hic.</NOTE>
