<L N="296">Musynge on &thorn;is meteles &middot; a myle-wey ich &yogh;eode.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>on</I>] in M. <I>&thorn;is</I>] <I>miswritten</I> &thorn;ees P; <I>but see</I> l. 297. <I>&yogh;eode</I>] &yogh;ode I; &yogh;ede MEFG.</NOTE></L>
<L>And meny tymes this meteles &middot; made me to studie<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] IG <I>om. tymes</I>] time IMF. <I>made</I>] ha&thorn; maked I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of &thorn;at ich seih slepynge &middot; yf hit so be myghte,</L>
<L>And of peers plouhman &middot; [ful] pensyf in herte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>peers</I>] peres &thorn;e I. [<I>ful</I> IFG] PEM <I>om.; cf.</I> B-text.</NOTE></L>
<L>And which a pardon peers hadde &middot; the puple to gladen,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>which</I>] wich P. <I>a</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="301">And how &thorn;e preest inpugned hit &middot; thorwe two propre wordes.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>thorwe</I>] with F.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac men setten nat by songewarie &middot; men seen hit ofte faile,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ac</I>] And G. <I>men</I> (2)] for men I; <I>miswritten</I> mei P. <I>hit</I>] M <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Caton counte&thorn; hit at nouht &middot; and canonistres at lasse.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>counte&thorn;</I>] a-counte&thorn; M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="304">Ac for &thorn;e bok bible &middot; bere&thorn; good wyttnesse,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bok</I>] goode G. <I>good</I>] I <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>How daniel dyuinede &middot; and vndude &thorn;e dremeles<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="100"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vndude</I>] <I>so</I> PM; vndede FG; vndide I; vnded E. <I>dremeles</I>] dremes IF. I <I>adds</I> of kynges, <I>omit|ting</I> kyng <I>in</I> l. 306.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of kyng nabugodonosor &middot; &thorn;at no peer hadde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hadde</I>] ne hadde M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And sitthe after to hus sones &middot; seide hem what &thorn;ei thouhte:&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] G <I>om. to</I>] I <I>om. seidc</I>] and saide I; told F.</NOTE></L>
<L N="308">And Ioseph mette meruelousliche &middot; how &thorn;e mone and &thorn;e sonne<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mette</I> IMFEG] mete P.</NOTE></L>
<L>And elleuene sterres &middot; hailsede hym alle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>elleuene</I>] &thorn;e enleuene I; also elleue F. <I>hailsede</I>] heilede M; hei|seden (<I>sic</I>) F; hail seide to G.</NOTE></L>
<L>Thenne Iacob Iuged &middot; Iosephes sweuene:<MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="120"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Thenne</I>] And &thorn;enne G.</NOTE></L>
<L>"Beau fitz," qua&thorn; &thorn;e fader &middot; "we shulle&thorn; for defaute,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Beau</I>] Bew M. <I>fitz</I>] filtz M; fiz G. <I>we&mdash;defaute</I>] for defaute we schal I.</NOTE></L>
<L N="312">Ich my-self and my sones &middot; seche [&thorn;e] for neede;"<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>&thorn;e</I> IFMEG] P <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Hit by-fel as &thorn;e fader seide &middot; in [pharaoes] tyme,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I>] his F. [<I>pharaoes</I> MFE] pharoes G; Pharao I; pharao hus P.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at Ioseph was Iustice &middot; egipte to saue;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to</I>] for to EF.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00001013.tif" N="175, C-text"></L>
<L>Hus eleuene bro&thorn;eres &middot; hym for neede souhte,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bro&thorn;eres</I>] bre&thorn;eres E; bre&thorn;eren IF; bre&thorn;erne M; bre&thorn;ren G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="316">And hus fader Iacob &middot; and al-so hus dame:&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Iacob</I>] Isaac (!) I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Al &thorn;is make&thorn; me &middot; on meteles to studie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>meteles</I>] metinge G.</NOTE></L>
<L>And how &thorn;e preest preuede &middot; no pardon to do-wel;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>preuede</I> IG] prouede MEF; preeued P. <I>to</I>] but M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And demede &thorn;at dowel &middot; Indulgences passede,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>demede &thorn;at</I>] &thorn;e mede of (!) E. <I>Indulgences</I>] indulgence MF. <I>pas|sede</I>] passe&thorn; I.</NOTE></L>
<L N="320">Byennals and tryennals &middot; and bisshopes letteres.</L>
<L>For ho so do&thorn; wel here &middot; at &thorn;e daye of dome<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="101"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>do&thorn; wel</I> MEFG] dowel I; wel do&thorn; P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Worth faire vnderfonge &middot; by-for god &thorn;at tyme.</L>
<L>So dowel passe&thorn; pardon &middot; and pilgrimages to rome;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pilgrimages</I>] pilgrimage IM. <I>to</I>] of G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="324">&YOGH;ut hath &thorn;e pope power &middot; pardon to graunte<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hath&mdash;pope</I>] ha&thorn; &thorn;e popus F; han &thorn;e popes E (<I>observe this read|ing</I>). <I>pardon</I>] &thorn;e pardone G.</NOTE></L>
<L>To puple, with-oute penaunce &middot; to passen in-to Ioye,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>puple</I>] &thorn;e peple EF. <I>to</I>] G <I>om. in-to</I>] to F.</NOTE></L>
<L>As lettred men ous lere&thorn; &middot; and lawe of holy churche:<Q><I>Quodcunque ligaueris super terram erit ligatum &amp; in celis; Et quodcunque solueris super terram erit solutum &amp; in celis.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lero&thorn;</I>] lered I. <I>lawe</I>] men MG. <I>Et&mdash;celis</I>] MIFG <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>And so ich by-leyue leelly &middot; lordes forbode elles,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>by-leyue</I>] by-leue P (<I>here; but</I> by-leyue <I>elsewhere</I>); leue EIG; leeue F. <I>lordes</I>] goddes F. <I>lordes forbode</I>] lord forbede EI; lord me for-beode M.</NOTE></L>
<L N="328">&THORN;at pardon and penaunce &middot; and preieres don saue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>penaunce</I>] penaunces I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Saule[s] &thorn;at han synged &middot; seuene sithe[s] dedliche.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Saules</I> E] Soules MIFG; Saule P. <I>synged</I>] singed G; synned IEF; i-synned M. <I>sithes</I> IFG] sithe PE; times M.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac to trysten vpon triennels &middot; treweliche me thynke&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vpon</I>] apon P; vp &thorn;is I. <I>treweliche</I>] triweliche P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ys nat so syker for &thorn;e saule &middot; certys, as ys dowel.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ys</I>] Nys M; It is I. <I>for</I>] to I. <I>ys</I>] I (<I>sic</I>) I; M <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>For-thi ich rede &yogh;ow renkes &middot; &thorn;at riche ben on &thorn;ys erthe,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For-thi</I>] For-whi M. <I>renkes</I>] ruleres G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="333">Vp trist of &yogh;oure tresour &middot; tryennels to haue,</L>
<L>Be &yogh;e neuere &thorn;e boldere &middot; to breke &thorn;e ten hestes;
<PB REF="00001014.tif" N="176, C-text"></L>
<L>And nameliche, &yogh;e maistres &middot; meyres and Iuges,<MILESTONE UNIT="B page" N="121"></L>
<L N="336">That han &thorn;e welthe of &thorn;is worlde &middot; and wise men ben holde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>holde</I>] i-holde M; holden G.</NOTE></L>
<L>To purchace &yogh;ow pardon &middot; and &thorn;e popes bulles.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;ow</I>] &yogh;oure I.</NOTE></L>
<L>At &thorn;e dredful day of dome &middot; when dede men shullen ryse,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>day of</I>] I <I>om. men</I>] I <I>om. ryse</I>] a-risen MIG.</NOTE></L>
<L>And comen alle by-fore crist &middot; a-countes to &yogh;elde,</L>
<L>Howe we ladde oure lyf here &middot; and hus lawes kepte,</L>
<L>And how we dude day by day &middot; &thorn;e dome wol reherce.<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="102"></L>
<L N="342">A poke-ful of pardon &thorn;ere &middot; ne prouincials letteres,</L>
<L>&THORN;auh [we] be founde in fraternite &middot; of alle fyue ordres,<NOTE PLACE="foot">[<I>we</I> IG] he PMEF (<I>observe</I> ous <I>in</I> l. 344). <I>in</I>] in &thorn;e IM. <I>fyue</I>] &thorn;e fyue MF.</NOTE></L>
<L N="344">And haue indulgences doblefolde &middot; bote dowel ous helpe,</L>
<L>Ich sette by pardon nat a peese &middot; no&thorn;er a pye hele!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>by&mdash;nat</I>] noght by pardoun I. <I>no&thorn;er</I>] ne nat I; ne M. <I>hele</I> IMEG] heele F; hyle P.</NOTE></L>
<L>For-thi ich counsaile alle cristine &middot; to crye god mercy,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For-thi</I>] For-whi M. <I>crye god</I>] god to cri&yogh;e M; crye god of F.</NOTE></L>
<L>And marye hus moder &middot; be oure mene to hym,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>marye</I>] to mari&yogh;e M. <I>moder</I>] deere modur F. <I>be</I>] to be F. <I>oure&mdash;hym</I>] to him oure mene G.</NOTE></L>
<L N="348">&THORN;at god &yogh;eue ous grace here &middot; er we go hennes,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>go hennes</I>] hennes wende I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Suche workes to worche &middot; whil we ben here,<NOTE PLACE="foot">I <I>omits. whil</I>] while &thorn;at F.</NOTE></L>
<L>That after oure de&thorn;-day &middot; dowel reherce</L>
<L>At &thorn;e day of dome &middot; we dude as he tauhte.&mdash;<I>Amen.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>At</I>] &THORN;at at G. <I>day</I>] dredful day F. <I>tauhte</I>] us tau&yogh;te M. <I>Amen</I>] M <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<TRAILER><I>Hic explicit uisio willelmi de petro plouhman.</I><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hic</I>] EMIF <I>om. wil|lelmi</I>] Willelmi W. (<I>sic</I>) I; G <I>om. plouhman</I>] le Plowman I. <I>See</I> Pre|face. <I>The title</I> Incipit uisio eiusdem, &amp;c. <I>immediately follows; see</I> Pass. xi.</NOTE></TRAILER>
</LG>


