<L>And art so loth to leue &middot; &thorn;at leue shalt needes:<Q><I>O stulte, ista nocte anima tua egredietur;</I> [<I>que congregasti, cuius erunt?</I>] <I>Thesaurizat, &amp; ignorat</I> [<I>cui, &amp;c.</I>].</Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>art</I>] ert PEK. <I>leue</I>] lene <I>or</I> leue <I>in the MSS.</I> I <I>has</I>&mdash;And art so loth to leue &middot; &thorn;at lete schal &thorn;ou nedes; <I>so</I> T (<I>with</I> shalt <I>for</I> schal &thorn;ou). <I>shalt</I>] schal &thorn;ou I; &thorn;ou schalt FS. <I>egredietur</I> EG] egrediatur PITKM; rapietur F; rapietur a te S. [<I>que&mdash;erunt</I>] <I>in</I> E <I>only.</I> [<I>cui</I>] <I>in</I> S <I>only.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="216">An vnredy reue &middot; &thorn;i residue shal spene,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>spene</I>] spende T; haue M.</NOTE>
