<L>Thauh &thorn;e messager make hus wey &middot; a-mydde &thorn;e whete,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>amydde</I>] amyde P; amonge T. <I>whete</I>] fayre whete IT.</NOTE></L>
<L N="44">Wole no wys man wroth be &middot; ne hus wed take;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wroth be</I>] be wroth ITKFS.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00001071.tif" N="233, C-text"></L>
<L>Ys non haiwarde yhote &middot; hus wed for to take;<Q><I>Necessitas non habet legem.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ys</I>] Ne T. <I>yhote</I>] hote I; is hoten T. <I>to</I>] K <I>om. take</I>] nyme M. <I>Most MSS. agree in making lines</I> 44 <I>and</I> 45 <I>end nearly alike; but</I> ITKFG <I>insert</I> Necessitas&mdash;legem <I>between them;</I> M <I>omits this quotation alto|gether.</I></NOTE></L>
