<L>For reson wolde haue reherced to &thorn;e &middot; ryght as cleregie seide;<MILESTONE UNIT="A page" N="190"><NOTE PLACE="foot">M <I>omits. to</I>] IKT <I>omit.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Ac for &thorn;yn entermetyng &middot; her art &thorn;ow for-sake:<Q><I>Philosophus fuisses, si tacuisses; et alibi: Locutum me aliquando penituit, tacuisse nunquam.</I></Q><NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><I>Ac</I>] T <I>om. her</I>] &thorn;er E. <I>art</I> MKST] ert PE. <I>art &thorn;ow</I>] artow I. S <I>has</I> &mdash; Si tacuisses, philosophus fuisses; Me aliquando locutum fuisse penituit, siluisse nunquam. <I>me</I>] est (<I>wrongly; for</I> esse) M.</P><P>OBS. One leaf <I>lost in</I> G, <I>down to</I> xv. 40.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>Adam, whiles he spak nat &middot; hadde paradys at wylle;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whiles</I>] &thorn;e whiles IT; while M. <I>nat</I>] nout M. <I>at</I>] att P.</NOTE></L>
<L N="228">Ac whanne he mamelede a-boute mete &middot; and musede for to knowe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>whanne</I>] wanne P. <I>mame|lede</I>] momelede S. <I>and</I>] he T. <I>for</I>] T <I>om.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>The wisdome and &thorn;e wit of God &middot; he was putte out of blisse.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wit</I>] witt P.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ryght so ferde reson by &thorn;e &middot; for &thorn;i rude speche,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ferde</I>] fari&thorn; T. <I>rude</I>] proude M.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for &thorn;ow woldest wyte why &middot; of resones pryuete.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>woldest wyte</I>] wost ywite (<I>sic</I>) E. <I>of&mdash;pryuete</I>] resones preuede (<I>sic</I>) I; resoun is preuyte T.</NOTE></L>
<L N="232">For pruyde and presompcion &middot; of &thorn;y parfit lyuynge<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>For</I>] IT <I>om. and</I>] or IT.</NOTE></L>
<L>Reson refusede &thorn;e &middot; and wolde nat reste with the,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wolde</I>] wul S.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne cleregie of hus connynge &middot; kepe&thorn; &thorn;e nat shewe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hus</I>] E <I>om. &thorn;e</I>] I <I>om. nat</I>] not to T.</NOTE></L>
<L>For shal neuere, er shame come &middot; a shrewe wel be chasted;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wel</I>] K <I>om. chasted</I>] ychasted EK. <I>be chasted</I>] chaste IT.</NOTE></L>
<L N="236">For let a dronken daffe &middot; in a diche falle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>diche</I>] dike I.</NOTE></L>
<L>Let hym lygge, lok nat [on] hym &middot; til hym luste aryse;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Let</I> MKST] Late I; Leet P. [<I>on</I> IMKST] in PE. <I>luste</I>] liste ET; luste to M; lust to IS. <I>aryse</I>] rise I.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;auh reson rebuke hym &thorn;enne &middot; recche&thorn; he neuere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] For IMKST. <I>rebuke</I> IMKST] rebuky P. <I>he</I>] &yogh;e S.</NOTE></L>
