<L N="8">And no tyme to [tyne] &middot; ne trewe &thorn;yng to teenen;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>And</I>] Ne IT. <I>to</I> (1)] T <I>om.</I> [<I>tyne</I> EMIKTS] tene P. <I>trewe</I>] trywe P. <I>to</I> (2)] IT <I>om. teenen</I>] tenen E; teone K; tene MITS.</NOTE></L>
<L>Lowe &thorn;e to lyue forth &middot; in &thorn;e lawe of holychurche;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to</I>] and to M; and ITK; for to S. <I>lyue</I>] &thorn;e lynde (!) E.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;enne dost &thorn;ow wel, with-oute drede &middot; ho can do bet, no forse!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&THORN;enne</I>] And &thorn;anne IT. <I>bet</I>] bett PI.</NOTE></L>
